1
00:03:36,395 --> 00:03:38,770
My lord.
The enemy is at our door.

2
00:03:38,936 --> 00:03:41,895
Are the Ottomans so cruel as
to interrupt our love?

3
00:03:42,686 --> 00:03:45,186
And they will pay for it,
my beloved.

4
00:03:49,728 --> 00:03:50,811
Come on!

5
00:03:55,478 --> 00:03:57,061
Mmm-mm.

6
00:04:01,561 --> 00:04:03,103
Is this war necessary?

7
00:04:04,228 --> 00:04:06,770
Can't we all live in peace as
God intends for us?

8
00:04:07,645 --> 00:04:10,895
You are my reason for being,
Elizabeta...

9
00:04:10,978 --> 00:04:13,811
Please take care of
yourself my king...

10
00:04:14,061 --> 00:04:15,145
...my life...

11
00:04:16,478 --> 00:04:19,103
Because I cannot
survive without you.

12
00:04:46,436 --> 00:04:47,478
That's enough, my lord.

13
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:49,603
War calls, victory's yours!

14
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:52,686
My men will take you to
Vilmür Castle, to our cousins.

15
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:53,811
You will be safe here.

16
00:05:07,478 --> 00:05:11,186
Princeps invictus et
iustarum animarum...

17
00:05:11,895 --> 00:05:14,061
...nos in proelio defendamus.

18
00:05:25,853 --> 00:05:26,728
Amen.

19
00:05:26,770 --> 00:05:29,228
This battle will be bloody,
your eminence.

20
00:05:30,353 --> 00:05:32,728
The dead will number
in the thousands.

21
00:05:35,436 --> 00:05:37,478
Are you sure God will this?

22
00:05:37,561 --> 00:05:40,395
Our kingdom is the last bastion
against the Muslims.

23
00:05:40,728 --> 00:05:43,145
- Do you have faith in our lord?
- I do.

24
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:45,645
I'm ready to die for him.

25
00:05:45,728 --> 00:05:48,228
Then hunt these barbarians
to the last man.

26
00:05:49,478 --> 00:05:53,270
I will fight in his name,
but I ask him for one favor.

27
00:05:54,603 --> 00:05:55,770
I'm listening, my son.

28
00:06:02,603 --> 00:06:04,395
I want him to spare my wife.

29
00:06:05,061 --> 00:06:07,977
If she doesn't survive,
I won't be able to go on.

30
00:06:08,977 --> 00:06:12,478
Everything would lose meaning.
Life would become unbearable.

31
00:06:13,353 --> 00:06:15,353
Calm yourself,
you risk basphemy!

32
00:06:16,395 --> 00:06:18,811
Lord gave you life.
You must honour and serve him.

33
00:06:18,895 --> 00:06:20,853
But he gave me love as well.

34
00:06:22,228 --> 00:06:25,520
He cannot blame me for
being unable to live without it.

35
00:06:26,603 --> 00:06:27,977
If he takes her life...

36
00:06:28,561 --> 00:06:30,103
...he can take mine too.

37
00:06:33,145 --> 00:06:34,686
I will pray for your request.

38
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:36,728
No. Don't pray.

39
00:06:37,311 --> 00:06:38,395
Tell him.

40
00:06:43,936 --> 00:06:45,061
For the prince!

41
00:08:05,061 --> 00:08:06,936
They're here in the forest...

42
00:08:14,103 --> 00:08:15,520
What is your plan sir?

43
00:08:19,395 --> 00:08:20,561
Let them come...

44
00:08:49,811 --> 00:08:51,645
Go Princess! go!

45
00:08:51,686 --> 00:08:54,478
Run! Save yourself!

46
00:08:58,353 --> 00:08:59,770
Pierce the barrels!

47
00:08:59,853 --> 00:09:02,145
Pierce the barrels!

48
00:10:32,770 --> 00:10:36,061
Vlad?! Vlad, the Princess!

49
00:10:37,061 --> 00:10:38,145
Speak!

50
00:10:38,478 --> 00:10:39,728
There was an ambush...

51
00:10:39,895 --> 00:10:40,977
...she managed to escape!

52
00:10:41,228 --> 00:10:42,270
Where did she go?

53
00:10:42,895 --> 00:10:44,103
The forest of wolves.

54
00:10:52,853 --> 00:10:54,603
No!!

55
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:42,770
No!!

56
00:12:43,061 --> 00:12:44,103
My Prince!!

57
00:12:48,061 --> 00:12:48,977
No.

58
00:13:49,977 --> 00:13:50,936
My wife...

59
00:13:51,478 --> 00:13:52,436
...is dead.

60
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:55,395
We've been praying
for her since you left.

61
00:13:55,603 --> 00:13:56,977
So God is deaf?

62
00:13:57,977 --> 00:14:00,061
Or you did not pray hard enough!

63
00:14:00,395 --> 00:14:01,603
My Prince.

64
00:14:02,020 --> 00:14:05,686
God has his own reasons,
it is not for us to question them.

65
00:14:06,561 --> 00:14:08,311
Perhaps he had
another destiny for her.

66
00:14:08,436 --> 00:14:11,478
She has no other destiny!
She is dead!!

67
00:14:11,603 --> 00:14:14,728
And he didn't even allow me
to say goodbye to her!

68
00:14:15,270 --> 00:14:16,395
I beg you...

69
00:14:16,895 --> 00:14:18,770
...tell God to send her back to me.

70
00:14:18,853 --> 00:14:20,020
It's impossible.

71
00:14:20,061 --> 00:14:20,978
Why?

72
00:14:21,977 --> 00:14:22,770
Why?!

73
00:14:22,853 --> 00:14:26,270
Because God does not perform
reincarnation.

74
00:14:26,436 --> 00:14:28,770
But he can perform miracle,
can he not?

75
00:14:29,561 --> 00:14:30,603
Can he not?

76
00:14:31,478 --> 00:14:34,645
If you pray hard enough,
he will listen to you.

77
00:14:36,103 --> 00:14:38,061
Please tell him.

78
00:14:39,103 --> 00:14:40,270
Tell him!

79
00:14:40,977 --> 00:14:44,436
She... she was a good
Christian and a pure soul.

80
00:14:45,561 --> 00:14:48,103
I'm sure God will take care of her.

81
00:14:48,145 --> 00:14:49,436
And what about me?

82
00:14:49,977 --> 00:14:52,186
I've done everything he has asked.

83
00:14:52,478 --> 00:14:54,270
My soul is stained with the
blood of our enemies...

84
00:14:54,353 --> 00:14:56,728
...whom I have killed in his name.

85
00:14:56,811 --> 00:14:58,895
I don't have the answers, my Prince.

86
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:02,186
I'm only his humble messenger.

87
00:15:02,686 --> 00:15:03,478
Good...

88
00:15:03,645 --> 00:15:06,977
I have a message that
I want you to deliver to him.

89
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:18,395
Tell your God...

90
00:15:18,936 --> 00:15:21,478
...that until he brings me
back my wife...

91
00:15:21,895 --> 00:15:24,228
...my life no longer belongs to him.

92
00:15:58,645 --> 00:15:59,603
When did he arrived?

93
00:15:59,811 --> 00:16:01,186
Around ten minutes ago.

94
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:02,853
Okay.

95
00:16:03,270 --> 00:16:04,228
Where did you leave him?

96
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:05,728
In the Chapel.

97
00:16:05,811 --> 00:16:07,603
- It seemed most appropriate.
- You did the right thing...

98
00:16:07,645 --> 00:16:08,977
You did the right thing.

99
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:18,936
Let him finish praying...

100
00:16:23,770 --> 00:16:24,770
Father?

101
00:16:25,561 --> 00:16:26,228
Ah!

102
00:16:26,978 --> 00:16:29,228
- Dr. Dumont, I presume?
- Yes.

103
00:16:29,811 --> 00:16:31,603
You have a very beautiful chapel.

104
00:16:32,853 --> 00:16:33,811
Yes, it's true.

105
00:16:33,977 --> 00:16:35,728
Thank you for making this trip,
Father.

106
00:16:35,811 --> 00:16:37,686
It must have been a long
and arduous journey.

107
00:16:37,728 --> 00:16:39,436
Exhausting, I must admit.

108
00:16:40,061 --> 00:16:43,395
That's why I'm partaking of some
light refreshment I found right here.

109
00:16:43,478 --> 00:16:44,561
I hope you don't mind?

110
00:16:44,977 --> 00:16:46,853
- Not at all.
- You're most kind.

111
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:51,728
I'm sure it tastes much better than
the beer in my native Bavaria.

112
00:16:51,811 --> 00:16:54,603
I'm sorry to welcome you in such
an ungracious manner, but...

113
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:57,520
I'm afraid the hospital
administration and diocese...

114
00:16:57,561 --> 00:16:59,145
...don't support your presence here.

115
00:16:59,228 --> 00:17:00,061
I'm used to it.

116
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:04,186
The church and the scientific academies
don't get along very well.

117
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:08,186
That's why the Vatican for centuries
has been in the habit of...

118
00:17:08,228 --> 00:17:11,936
...delegating its most
delicate cases to us.

119
00:17:12,645 --> 00:17:15,061
This case is very delicate.

120
00:17:15,145 --> 00:17:17,270
The Queen of England herself
is concerned.

121
00:17:17,478 --> 00:17:18,395
The Queen?

122
00:17:19,228 --> 00:17:20,061
Exciting...

123
00:17:26,561 --> 00:17:27,895
No. No, no...

124
00:17:28,561 --> 00:17:31,436
It's the ceremony of the centenary
of the French Revolution in...

125
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,311
...a few days.

126
00:17:32,353 --> 00:17:34,228
There's a lot of
excitement everywhere...

127
00:17:51,645 --> 00:17:53,228
Go down.

128
00:18:04,270 --> 00:18:05,186
Close the door.

129
00:18:12,020 --> 00:18:13,311
Why so many chains?

130
00:18:13,978 --> 00:18:15,561
Afraid she'll fly away?

131
00:18:15,853 --> 00:18:17,977
She was quite aggressive
when we picked her up.

132
00:18:18,353 --> 00:18:19,520
A real beast.

133
00:18:20,895 --> 00:18:23,728
Even animals are entitled to
a little humanity.

134
00:18:23,811 --> 00:18:25,186
What do we know about her?

135
00:18:26,186 --> 00:18:27,020
Please.

136
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:33,853
Maria de Montebello,
25 from Bologna, Italy...

137
00:18:34,311 --> 00:18:36,311
...engaged to marry
Henry William Spencer...

138
00:18:36,395 --> 00:18:39,686
...consul, here in Paris, and...

139
00:18:40,145 --> 00:18:41,811
...great-nephew, by marriage...

140
00:18:42,228 --> 00:18:43,436
...of the Queen herself.

141
00:18:43,603 --> 00:18:45,436
That's why this case
is so delicate?

142
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:47,520
More than delicate...
Sensitive.

143
00:18:47,561 --> 00:18:48,936
Anything else I should know?

144
00:18:49,186 --> 00:18:50,561
From what I've been told...

145
00:18:50,895 --> 00:18:53,645
...it all began during the wedding,
which took place...

146
00:18:53,936 --> 00:18:57,395
...on the family estate,
as Maria objected to a church.

147
00:18:57,895 --> 00:19:00,311
However the groom had invited...

148
00:19:00,561 --> 00:19:02,978
...the bishop of Westminster to
bless the union...

149
00:19:03,228 --> 00:19:05,936
...and at the sight of the
clergyman the bride...

150
00:19:06,436 --> 00:19:08,311
...was seized with hysteria

151
00:19:08,353 --> 00:19:10,977
...and a sexual appetite
beyond comprehension.

152
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:14,186
Appetites can be a sign of very good
health, can they not, doctor?

153
00:19:14,270 --> 00:19:15,978
Well, certainly, Within limits.

154
00:19:16,145 --> 00:19:17,395
- May I?
- Sure.

155
00:19:19,061 --> 00:19:22,645
Born on the
18th of March, 1759.

156
00:19:23,895 --> 00:19:25,853
It must be a clerical error.

157
00:19:25,936 --> 00:19:28,020
Otherwise it would mean
that she is...

158
00:19:28,061 --> 00:19:29,978
A hundred and 30 years old exactly.

159
00:19:30,853 --> 00:19:31,978
A hundred and...

160
00:19:34,145 --> 00:19:37,270
So you believe this woman
is a creature of devil?

161
00:19:37,936 --> 00:19:40,061
That's a hasty conclusion, doctor.

162
00:19:40,977 --> 00:19:43,976
Very often when a situation
escapes our understanding...

163
00:19:43,978 --> 00:19:46,395
...we see in it the
work of the devil.

164
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:51,395
Well, the fact that she's old and
allergic to God's representatives...

165
00:19:52,645 --> 00:19:55,186
...is merely a symptom,
not a disease.

166
00:19:55,978 --> 00:19:59,728
It is very important in
cases like this to study...

167
00:20:00,103 --> 00:20:02,103
...to observe without prejudice.

168
00:20:02,145 --> 00:20:03,561
We must follow...

169
00:20:03,853 --> 00:20:07,603
...the rules and laws of nature,
science, mathematics...

170
00:20:07,686 --> 00:20:10,395
...not those of superstition
or the church...

171
00:20:11,145 --> 00:20:13,770
...which I must admit
can be a trifle obscure.

172
00:20:13,811 --> 00:20:16,311
You see, doctor,
we have to approach this...

173
00:20:16,478 --> 00:20:18,103
...like a criminal investigation.

174
00:20:18,186 --> 00:20:19,728
First, we establish the fact.

175
00:20:20,145 --> 00:20:22,561
From there,
we deduce the motives...

176
00:20:23,061 --> 00:20:25,853
...the circumstances, the location.

177
00:20:26,645 --> 00:20:27,686
Could you hold this please?

178
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:31,020
And the murder weapon.

179
00:20:33,936 --> 00:20:37,853
My order has been studying this
phenomenon for more than 400 years.

180
00:20:37,936 --> 00:20:39,436
I personally, for more than 30.

181
00:20:40,520 --> 00:20:43,145
And I can state for the record,
doctor, you are the first...

182
00:20:43,186 --> 00:20:45,645
...one to have captured
a specimen alive.

183
00:20:46,520 --> 00:20:47,728
Congratulations.

184
00:20:48,186 --> 00:20:49,395
Thank you... I...

185
00:20:51,270 --> 00:20:52,977
What exactly did I capture?

186
00:20:53,186 --> 00:20:54,186
A vampire.

187
00:20:54,395 --> 00:20:56,311
Don't listen to him, doctor.

188
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:58,478
Help me...

189
00:20:58,686 --> 00:21:00,478
I'll let you do whatever you want.

190
00:21:07,145 --> 00:21:08,103
Smile, please.

191
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:13,561
The oversize canines could
be a clue...

192
00:21:13,977 --> 00:21:16,478
...but they could also be
a natural explanation.

193
00:21:18,436 --> 00:21:19,853
So we must look elsewhere.

194
00:21:21,561 --> 00:21:23,936
This creature, like any other...

195
00:21:23,977 --> 00:21:26,395
...is definitely the
work of our Lord.

196
00:21:26,478 --> 00:21:28,395
But for some mysterious reason...

197
00:21:28,436 --> 00:21:31,686
...it seems God may have
other plans with it.

198
00:21:33,270 --> 00:21:36,353
Contrary to popular belief,
vampires adapt...

199
00:21:36,395 --> 00:21:38,311
...very well to light in general.

200
00:21:38,353 --> 00:21:41,270
But it is direct rays
they cannot take.

201
00:21:47,061 --> 00:21:49,103
This is crazy.
It doesn't make any sense.

202
00:21:49,353 --> 00:21:50,977
Again, you may be right.

203
00:21:51,103 --> 00:21:53,603
This could be just another
anomaly of nature.

204
00:21:53,686 --> 00:21:57,770
So we have to continue until
we find irrefutable proof.

205
00:22:02,436 --> 00:22:05,103
Well, I think we have
all the proof we need.

206
00:22:05,145 --> 00:22:06,270
Doctor, don't you?

207
00:22:08,436 --> 00:22:10,561
This is beyond science
and understanding.

208
00:22:10,978 --> 00:22:12,770
- Uh!
- That's why I am here.

209
00:22:19,020 --> 00:22:20,520
My dear child...

210
00:22:21,645 --> 00:22:23,020
...may I call you Maria?

211
00:22:24,478 --> 00:22:25,603
Of course.

212
00:22:26,478 --> 00:22:28,853
You can call me as you like, father.

213
00:22:29,311 --> 00:22:31,020
I'm all yours.

214
00:22:32,977 --> 00:22:34,936
Maria, if you answer
my questions nicely...

215
00:22:34,977 --> 00:22:36,728
...I will give you what you want.

216
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:39,311
You know my desires.

217
00:22:39,395 --> 00:22:40,311
I know your needs.

218
00:22:40,395 --> 00:22:41,811
- Mmm.
- Allow me.

219
00:22:43,645 --> 00:22:45,103
Come a little closer my son.

220
00:22:45,561 --> 00:22:47,645
Science requires sacrifice.

221
00:22:47,686 --> 00:22:49,061
Are you ready to make one?

222
00:22:49,603 --> 00:22:51,020
- I suppose so.
- Good boy.

223
00:22:52,478 --> 00:22:53,520
What are you doing?

224
00:22:53,645 --> 00:22:56,645
A few drops of blood.
A meager contribution to science.

225
00:22:56,728 --> 00:22:59,103
I'll buy you a lentil soup,
you'll feel like a new man.

226
00:22:59,186 --> 00:23:00,145
Uh-uh.

227
00:23:03,978 --> 00:23:04,811
Thank you.

228
00:23:07,645 --> 00:23:08,811
Thank you.

229
00:23:10,811 --> 00:23:12,270
Uh.

230
00:23:12,770 --> 00:23:13,603
Mm.

231
00:23:14,561 --> 00:23:16,853
Maria.
Show me your neck, please.

232
00:23:19,770 --> 00:23:22,561
You see, she's not
a first generation vampire.

233
00:23:22,853 --> 00:23:24,977
So you mean there
could be more of them?

234
00:23:25,478 --> 00:23:26,520
Without a doubt.

235
00:23:26,686 --> 00:23:29,645
For 400 years now,
we've been looking for the source.

236
00:23:29,770 --> 00:23:31,478
- The source?
- Yes.

237
00:23:31,603 --> 00:23:33,103
My master.

238
00:23:38,895 --> 00:23:39,936
Who is he?

239
00:23:42,186 --> 00:23:42,977
What's his name?

240
00:23:45,853 --> 00:23:47,061
Where can we find him?

241
00:23:47,145 --> 00:23:49,686
Oh, don't bother,
he'll find you.

242
00:23:49,770 --> 00:23:51,353
- He's here? In Paris?
- No.

243
00:23:51,395 --> 00:23:53,228
Very soon.

244
00:23:56,311 --> 00:23:58,228
Maria? Maria?

245
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,395
Maria!

246
00:24:02,478 --> 00:24:03,520
Who is he?

247
00:24:04,770 --> 00:24:06,061
He is a prince.

248
00:24:06,811 --> 00:24:07,603
A prince?

249
00:24:09,561 --> 00:24:11,228
He comes for the celebration?

250
00:24:11,311 --> 00:24:12,895
No...

251
00:24:14,478 --> 00:24:17,228
...he comes to find his princess.

252
00:24:18,228 --> 00:24:19,145
His princess?

253
00:24:20,353 --> 00:24:21,145
Who is she?

254
00:24:22,645 --> 00:24:24,811
- What does she look like?
- Mmm.

255
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:29,478
Very beautiful.

256
00:24:31,478 --> 00:24:32,936
More blood please.

257
00:24:32,977 --> 00:24:34,478
Ah!

258
00:24:34,645 --> 00:24:35,728
You had enough.

259
00:24:36,020 --> 00:24:37,270
More would be greedy.

260
00:24:38,811 --> 00:24:40,436
So, what is your conclusion?

261
00:24:40,936 --> 00:24:44,228
Now we can find a princess
who will lead us to her Prince.

262
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,353
Good luck.

263
00:25:12,728 --> 00:25:13,520
Are we there?

264
00:25:15,186 --> 00:25:17,228
Take this road. It is at the end.

265
00:25:17,311 --> 00:25:18,686
Can you help me with my luggage?

266
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:20,811
Can't leave my horses alone.

267
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:22,311
Too many wolves around.

268
00:25:23,061 --> 00:25:23,936
Glad to hear it.

269
00:25:23,977 --> 00:25:26,020
- Do you have a crucifix with you?
- Huh.

270
00:25:26,311 --> 00:25:27,228
No.

271
00:25:28,103 --> 00:25:30,520
Take mine.
Keep it always with you.

272
00:25:30,603 --> 00:25:31,645
Thank you, but...

273
00:25:31,811 --> 00:25:33,311
I do not believe in God.

274
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:35,353
Then pray God believes in you!

275
00:25:35,770 --> 00:25:36,728
Huh.

276
00:25:56,478 --> 00:25:58,061
Shhh! Shhh!

277
00:26:17,311 --> 00:26:18,145
Indeed.

278
00:26:55,103 --> 00:26:55,978
Hello?

279
00:27:24,395 --> 00:27:25,353
Is anybody here?

280
00:27:27,311 --> 00:27:28,061
Oh...

281
00:27:39,645 --> 00:27:40,478
Excuse me...

282
00:27:40,561 --> 00:27:41,436
I...

283
00:27:41,728 --> 00:27:42,603
You surprised me.

284
00:27:42,686 --> 00:27:45,645
It is I who apologize for my...

285
00:27:45,936 --> 00:27:47,270
Somewhat my...

286
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,103
...dramatic entrance.

287
00:27:52,145 --> 00:27:53,436
Give me this.

288
00:28:03,228 --> 00:28:04,061
Oh, uh.

289
00:28:04,311 --> 00:28:07,103
My apologies sir,
I didn't introduce myself.

290
00:28:07,436 --> 00:28:09,061
Jonathan Harker, solicitor.

291
00:28:09,103 --> 00:28:11,436
You're quite young for a lawyer.

292
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:14,811
Yes, I joined Phillips Law Office
in Paris earlier this year.

293
00:28:14,853 --> 00:28:16,353
Congratulations.

294
00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:17,520
Thank you.

295
00:28:18,061 --> 00:28:19,811
And, you are?

296
00:28:20,145 --> 00:28:21,645
Vlad the second...

297
00:28:22,728 --> 00:28:24,645
Prince of Wallachia...

298
00:28:26,895 --> 00:28:27,853
...Count...

299
00:28:28,977 --> 00:28:30,103
...Dracula.

300
00:28:36,186 --> 00:28:36,977
Oh?!

301
00:28:37,353 --> 00:28:40,395
Your Excellency - I apologize for
my clumsiness, I was given no...

302
00:28:40,436 --> 00:28:41,645
...physical description of you.

303
00:28:41,686 --> 00:28:43,603
My portrait is not well known.

304
00:28:43,686 --> 00:28:45,311
Except on these walls.

305
00:28:45,895 --> 00:28:46,977
Oh!

306
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:50,728
Magnificent!

307
00:28:51,895 --> 00:28:52,853
Is that a gramophone?

308
00:28:53,145 --> 00:28:54,728
Yes, it is.

309
00:28:54,936 --> 00:28:56,936
Uh!
I've never seen one before.

310
00:28:57,270 --> 00:29:00,186
- I'm very curious to...
- Later maybe.

311
00:29:01,186 --> 00:29:02,186
Let us dine.

312
00:29:02,561 --> 00:29:03,228
Fine.

313
00:29:08,645 --> 00:29:11,895
Oh, this is so good.

314
00:29:12,103 --> 00:29:15,728
Your appetite is a pleasure to see,
young man.

315
00:29:15,895 --> 00:29:17,895
Everything is so delicious and,
to be honest...

316
00:29:18,228 --> 00:29:19,853
I was starving to death! Huh.

317
00:29:22,978 --> 00:29:25,520
That certainly
won't be the case here.

318
00:29:25,977 --> 00:29:29,353
The upkeep of such an abode must
require countless amount of staff!

319
00:29:29,561 --> 00:29:30,395
Too many.

320
00:29:30,770 --> 00:29:33,020
And yet,
I am puzzled not to have seen any?

321
00:29:33,061 --> 00:29:34,561
They're very discreet.

322
00:29:35,853 --> 00:29:37,728
- You aren't eating?
- Later.

323
00:29:39,186 --> 00:29:40,353
Try this.

324
00:29:43,561 --> 00:29:44,561
Oh?

325
00:29:46,478 --> 00:29:47,395
Nice trick...

326
00:29:47,936 --> 00:29:48,853
Huh.

327
00:29:53,353 --> 00:29:54,728
Fantastic flavor!

328
00:29:54,977 --> 00:29:58,353
It is one of the recipes
I bring back from India.

329
00:29:58,436 --> 00:29:59,270
You travel a lot?

330
00:30:00,895 --> 00:30:02,478
Not anymore. But...

331
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,061
...once upon a time, yes...

332
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:10,686
...I visited every continent,
and crossed all oceans.

333
00:30:11,895 --> 00:30:12,603
Oh?!

334
00:30:12,645 --> 00:30:14,686
You must have so many wonderful
stories to tell then?

335
00:30:17,977 --> 00:30:18,686
I do.

336
00:30:19,686 --> 00:30:22,728
Were your travels for
work or pleasure?

337
00:30:23,561 --> 00:30:26,145
I handled certain affairs,
it is true...

338
00:30:26,353 --> 00:30:28,978
...but I'm retired now.

339
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:32,395
I let my...

340
00:30:33,478 --> 00:30:36,645
...associates travel around
the world in my place.

341
00:30:36,978 --> 00:30:38,145
And it's my associate...

342
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:40,436
...Mr Jenkins, who arranged
for my visit here.

343
00:30:40,936 --> 00:30:41,770
And, once again...

344
00:30:41,977 --> 00:30:43,977
...let me thank you for according me
a moment of your time...

345
00:30:44,311 --> 00:30:46,186
...I have plenty of time.

346
00:30:48,145 --> 00:30:48,977
So...

347
00:30:49,395 --> 00:30:51,686
...what brings you here, young man?

348
00:30:53,186 --> 00:30:54,020
Well...

349
00:30:54,936 --> 00:30:57,728
...among the many properties
that you own in Europe...

350
00:30:58,270 --> 00:30:59,603
...there is one in particular...

351
00:31:00,436 --> 00:31:03,395
...uh an old abbey,
in the heart of Paris.

352
00:31:03,977 --> 00:31:06,311
The county, which we represent...

353
00:31:06,853 --> 00:31:09,895
...wondered, given the
dilapidated state of the property...

354
00:31:09,977 --> 00:31:11,645
...if you might be interested
in selling?

355
00:31:12,228 --> 00:31:12,936
Uh.

356
00:31:12,977 --> 00:31:13,977
I think it's this one.

357
00:31:14,895 --> 00:31:16,186
No, not this one.

358
00:31:17,977 --> 00:31:20,977
Sorry. I must admit, the road...

359
00:31:21,103 --> 00:31:24,478
...was quite chaotic to get here
and my stuff is all upside down.

360
00:31:25,186 --> 00:31:27,020
And what do they
want to do with it?

361
00:31:27,811 --> 00:31:29,020
A hospital, I believe.

362
00:31:29,103 --> 00:31:31,561
The great Paris Exhibition
is coming soon...

363
00:31:31,977 --> 00:31:33,978
...and the city will
receive millions of visitors...

364
00:31:34,436 --> 00:31:36,103
Euh... Not this one...

365
00:31:36,353 --> 00:31:38,520
It's located near
Saint-Germain-Des-Près...

366
00:31:38,645 --> 00:31:40,103
Not too far from
the river la Seine...

367
00:31:40,145 --> 00:31:42,228
...I will... I will show you.

368
00:31:42,436 --> 00:31:43,977
Are you a believer?

369
00:31:45,186 --> 00:31:46,395
Sorry. What did you say?

370
00:31:46,436 --> 00:31:47,936
Do you believe in god?

371
00:31:50,020 --> 00:31:52,270
Not really.
The Coachman gave it to me.

372
00:31:52,728 --> 00:31:54,728
Old superstitions
run deep I suppose.

373
00:31:54,811 --> 00:31:55,395
Uh!

374
00:31:56,645 --> 00:31:57,520
Ah!

375
00:32:02,103 --> 00:32:02,811
Uh!

376
00:32:03,853 --> 00:32:04,811
Got it!

377
00:32:06,728 --> 00:32:09,061
Enough talking for tonight!

378
00:32:09,103 --> 00:32:10,686
Let me show you to your room.

379
00:32:23,436 --> 00:32:27,103
The castle is well guarded, but I
prefer you do not leave your room.

380
00:32:27,145 --> 00:32:29,270
Under any circumstances.

381
00:32:30,270 --> 00:32:32,728
Forgive me but...
what exactly are you afraid of?

382
00:32:32,811 --> 00:32:37,103
Old castles like this are filled
with memories that might haunt you.

383
00:32:37,395 --> 00:32:39,520
Oh, I'm not superstitious.

384
00:32:44,061 --> 00:32:46,020
That is a pity.

385
00:33:39,395 --> 00:33:40,311
Watch him.

386
00:33:58,811 --> 00:33:59,977
Elizabeta...

387
00:34:04,228 --> 00:34:04,977
Good evening.

388
00:34:05,020 --> 00:34:06,311
How may I help you, Father?

389
00:34:06,353 --> 00:34:09,353
I'd like to speak to
Mr. Henry William Spencer, please.

390
00:34:10,478 --> 00:34:11,145
Yes?

391
00:34:11,353 --> 00:34:14,061
My apologies for disturbing
at such a late hour...

392
00:34:14,270 --> 00:34:15,853
...but I was sent by a friend...

393
00:34:15,895 --> 00:34:18,520
...Doctor Dumont of
the Hôtel-Dieu Hospital.

394
00:34:18,770 --> 00:34:20,728
Oh God.
The hospital where Maria is?

395
00:34:20,811 --> 00:34:21,395
Indeed.

396
00:34:21,478 --> 00:34:22,811
Has something awful befallen her?

397
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:23,976
Yes! No! I mean...

398
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:25,936
...she's alive, clinically speaking.

399
00:34:26,228 --> 00:34:28,686
Oh. Thank God. Please come...

400
00:34:29,061 --> 00:34:29,770
...and sit down.

401
00:34:29,811 --> 00:34:31,811
Tell me everything, Father.

402
00:34:32,395 --> 00:34:33,436
I'm worried sick.

403
00:34:33,977 --> 00:34:35,311
Is her health stable, at least?

404
00:34:35,478 --> 00:34:38,061
She doesn't eat much,
drinks reasonably well...

405
00:34:38,145 --> 00:34:39,770
...yet she's bursting with energy.

406
00:34:41,853 --> 00:34:43,020
That bodes well.

407
00:34:43,061 --> 00:34:43,728
Hmm.

408
00:34:43,853 --> 00:34:44,686
That bodes...

409
00:34:44,977 --> 00:34:46,728
...very well,
yet... yet do we know more about...

410
00:34:46,811 --> 00:34:48,311
...this evil thing that's
eating away at her?

411
00:34:48,395 --> 00:34:49,395
We're making progress.

412
00:34:49,478 --> 00:34:52,977
But as you know, the science is
a long winding road that....

413
00:34:53,020 --> 00:34:56,103
...we can only travel step
by tiny step.

414
00:34:56,145 --> 00:34:57,936
You have a very nice place here.

415
00:34:58,145 --> 00:34:59,561
Yeah,
it belongs to the English crown.

416
00:34:59,603 --> 00:35:02,686
Yeah, the crown has always known
how to make good investment.

417
00:35:03,478 --> 00:35:04,853
What can I do for you, Father?

418
00:35:05,603 --> 00:35:06,977
I'd like to visit her room.

419
00:35:11,353 --> 00:35:12,645
May I ask what you're looking for?

420
00:35:12,686 --> 00:35:13,978
Nothing in particular.

421
00:35:14,061 --> 00:35:17,061
It's just important that
no stone be left unturned.

422
00:35:17,103 --> 00:35:19,436
You're a bit like an inspector
on a police investigation.

423
00:35:19,478 --> 00:35:20,311
Precisely.

424
00:35:20,395 --> 00:35:23,061
Except, I'm trying to solve
the case before the murder.

425
00:35:23,103 --> 00:35:24,353
Hmm.

426
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:25,811
I'll leave you to it...

427
00:35:28,311 --> 00:35:30,061
And if you ever need
any help in any occasion...

428
00:35:30,145 --> 00:35:31,061
...I'm your servant.

429
00:35:32,228 --> 00:35:34,270
Thank you.
That's very kind of you.

430
00:36:42,770 --> 00:36:43,770
There you are...

431
00:36:44,186 --> 00:36:46,311
Princess Elisabeta.

432
00:38:37,978 --> 00:38:40,145
You should not have left your room.

433
00:39:04,228 --> 00:39:05,186
Oh, my God.

434
00:39:06,686 --> 00:39:09,020
Don't utter that name.

435
00:39:10,311 --> 00:39:12,520
He is not welcome here.

436
00:39:12,770 --> 00:39:14,270
Are you the devil?

437
00:39:14,603 --> 00:39:16,978
God. Evil.

438
00:39:18,061 --> 00:39:20,728
Two almost identical entities.

439
00:39:20,936 --> 00:39:24,977
Two minds battling one another
without showing themselves.

440
00:39:25,478 --> 00:39:28,145
And we... we are their playthings.

441
00:39:29,478 --> 00:39:32,395
We are puppets that move
only and dare be haste.

442
00:39:32,978 --> 00:39:36,061
No! No! No!
No! No! No! No!

443
00:39:40,936 --> 00:39:42,103
Do you intend to kill me?

444
00:39:42,270 --> 00:39:43,228
I do.

445
00:39:44,145 --> 00:39:45,645
But not right away.

446
00:39:46,478 --> 00:39:50,061
It is important to wait until
the blood engorges the head.

447
00:39:50,728 --> 00:39:51,686
Who are you really?

448
00:39:51,977 --> 00:39:54,686
I am just a poor soul
condemned by God.

449
00:39:55,436 --> 00:39:58,977
And cursed to walk in the
shadow of death for all eternity.

450
00:40:00,686 --> 00:40:01,353
No!

451
00:40:01,436 --> 00:40:04,020
And sustain myself on fresh blood.

452
00:40:05,061 --> 00:40:07,061
Human blood is recommended.

453
00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:15,270
Ah!

454
00:40:15,561 --> 00:40:18,270
Why would God do such a thing?
He is only love and mercy.

455
00:40:18,603 --> 00:40:20,936
Oh,
I thought you were not a believer.

456
00:40:21,645 --> 00:40:23,645
- I am now.
- No!

457
00:40:37,895 --> 00:40:39,353
You are very funny

458
00:40:40,977 --> 00:40:41,936
Thank you.

459
00:40:42,270 --> 00:40:44,061
What is your last wish?

460
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:48,895
Euh...

461
00:40:51,728 --> 00:40:52,686
Tell me your story.

462
00:40:54,561 --> 00:40:55,686
My story?

463
00:40:56,270 --> 00:40:58,103
Yes.
Please.

464
00:40:58,436 --> 00:41:00,603
I want to know everything about you.

465
00:41:01,311 --> 00:41:03,520
This is your last wish.

466
00:41:03,977 --> 00:41:06,728
Is to listen to
a story from an old man.

467
00:41:07,436 --> 00:41:08,520
I'm dying to.

468
00:41:11,686 --> 00:41:12,728
You're dying to.

469
00:41:13,395 --> 00:41:14,645
It is very funny.

470
00:41:17,853 --> 00:41:19,145
Let's grant it then.

471
00:41:19,478 --> 00:41:20,686
Lower him down.

472
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:25,103
Lower him down.

473
00:41:39,561 --> 00:41:42,811
Life is nothing but a
long hard road, my friend.

474
00:41:43,936 --> 00:41:44,936
Death...

475
00:41:45,478 --> 00:41:47,977
...is a privilege that God
grants you...

476
00:41:49,020 --> 00:41:50,686
...and denies me.

477
00:41:51,977 --> 00:41:56,020
And yet, I was one of
his most faithful servants.

478
00:41:59,603 --> 00:42:00,561
What happened?

479
00:42:00,977 --> 00:42:02,186
He took my wife.

480
00:42:03,811 --> 00:42:05,270
My princess.

481
00:42:06,020 --> 00:42:07,478
The love of my life.

482
00:42:21,270 --> 00:42:22,395
Leave me alone.

483
00:42:34,936 --> 00:42:38,353
Since then, I've lived
on waiting for her return.

484
00:42:39,228 --> 00:42:41,520
How long exactly

485
00:42:42,728 --> 00:42:44,020
Four hundred years.

486
00:42:45,478 --> 00:42:47,103
That's pretty long.

487
00:42:48,561 --> 00:42:50,270
But how can you
be sure she'll come back?

488
00:42:54,020 --> 00:42:56,977
Sometimes pure souls
can be reincarnated.

489
00:42:58,603 --> 00:43:02,228
And my beloved was
the purest of them all.

490
00:43:04,895 --> 00:43:10,228
Forgive me, but I presume you
don't know when, where or how?

491
00:43:10,353 --> 00:43:11,686
Precisely.

492
00:43:14,561 --> 00:43:16,186
That doesn't seem like
a very good deal.

493
00:43:18,853 --> 00:43:20,186
That I have known.

494
00:43:20,603 --> 00:43:24,936
Sooner, young man, I would
have hired you as my lawyer.

495
00:43:25,061 --> 00:43:26,770
You've been looking for
all this time?

496
00:43:28,270 --> 00:43:30,311
The task has not been easy.

497
00:43:31,145 --> 00:43:35,520
The Black Base spread all
over Europe for centuries.

498
00:43:36,436 --> 00:43:39,561
Nearly 200 million souls
were decimated.

499
00:43:39,645 --> 00:43:41,061
Half of them women.

500
00:43:41,395 --> 00:43:44,603
This made my research
all the more difficult because...

501
00:43:45,145 --> 00:43:48,811
...all the remaining women were
gathered in holy places where...

502
00:43:49,186 --> 00:43:50,811
...I was not welcome.

503
00:43:56,061 --> 00:43:58,603
I was so lonely...

504
00:43:59,811 --> 00:44:04,811
...that I began to envy the
unfortunates that death claimed.

505
00:44:05,603 --> 00:44:09,395
Living without love is the
worst disease of all, my friend.

506
00:44:10,561 --> 00:44:11,895
It is like a fine...

507
00:44:12,686 --> 00:44:14,228
...incessant rain...

508
00:44:14,686 --> 00:44:17,770
...that gradually eats away
at your bones...

509
00:44:18,145 --> 00:44:20,977
...turning you into
a formless sponge...

510
00:44:21,436 --> 00:44:23,728
...unable to stand upright.

511
00:44:48,186 --> 00:44:51,103
And then, after a while...

512
00:44:51,936 --> 00:44:54,478
....no matter how strong
your love is...

513
00:44:55,853 --> 00:44:57,603
...you lose your faith.

514
00:45:19,936 --> 00:45:22,311
And yet they said that
hope is the spice of life.

515
00:45:23,061 --> 00:45:24,478
In my case...

516
00:45:25,020 --> 00:45:27,228
...I would prefer that...

517
00:45:28,978 --> 00:45:30,353
...hope kills me.

518
00:46:44,645 --> 00:46:47,061
To theibiline But, all
of this was of no use...

519
00:46:47,936 --> 00:46:51,436
...because God denied me
the right to die.

520
00:47:14,936 --> 00:47:18,811
Over time,
all desire disappears.

521
00:47:19,645 --> 00:47:22,478
Even the desire to end one's life.

522
00:47:23,228 --> 00:47:25,520
All you are left with is...

523
00:47:29,645 --> 00:47:31,561
...an orderless, charmless...

524
00:47:32,728 --> 00:47:33,853
...melancholy...

525
00:47:34,686 --> 00:47:38,811
...and the hope
that I will find her one day.

526
00:47:39,103 --> 00:47:43,686
But, I couldn't visit every
castle house in hamlet

527
00:47:45,061 --> 00:47:47,936
So, if I couldn't go to her....

528
00:47:48,561 --> 00:47:51,520
...I had to find a way for
her to come to me.

529
00:47:52,020 --> 00:47:52,853
How?

530
00:47:56,228 --> 00:47:56,895
Poison?

531
00:47:56,936 --> 00:47:59,603
Now look at this
who is being dramatic.

532
00:48:00,936 --> 00:48:04,520
It is a fragrance that I
developed for over a century.

533
00:48:05,020 --> 00:48:07,353
I visited the great city
of Baghdad...

534
00:48:08,311 --> 00:48:09,603
...known for its...

535
00:48:09,853 --> 00:48:13,270
....magical gardens of a
thousand and more flowers.

536
00:48:13,977 --> 00:48:18,436
Then I continued my journey
to Kanash...

537
00:48:18,895 --> 00:48:21,395
...in India, where I learned to...

538
00:48:21,478 --> 00:48:25,436
...capture the souls
of the most sensitive flowers.

539
00:48:27,020 --> 00:48:31,811
But it was only back in Europe
that my research came to fruition.

540
00:48:32,436 --> 00:48:36,853
First, to the colorful fields
of Grasse in France, where...

541
00:48:37,311 --> 00:48:42,311
...some flowers have intoxicated
our imaginations for centuries.

542
00:48:43,561 --> 00:48:47,270
And then, finally,
in the heart of Italy...

543
00:48:47,853 --> 00:48:50,895
...in the magnificent
city of Florence...

544
00:48:51,436 --> 00:48:54,478
...which was, at the time,
the capital of...

545
00:48:55,645 --> 00:48:57,270
...all the perfumes.

546
00:48:59,186 --> 00:49:02,311
Sir, I think this is it.

547
00:49:03,977 --> 00:49:05,811
The color is quite pleasant.

548
00:49:05,853 --> 00:49:07,395
Oh, never mind the color.

549
00:49:07,770 --> 00:49:10,977
The city is divine,
and the effect guarantees it.

550
00:49:11,145 --> 00:49:12,395
We shall see.

551
00:49:15,145 --> 00:49:19,978
Perhaps it would be wiser
to try outside.

552
00:49:20,853 --> 00:49:23,895
No, this seems to
be the ideal place.

553
00:49:29,811 --> 00:49:31,436
Oh, mamma mia.

554
00:49:37,311 --> 00:49:38,061
Uh.

555
00:49:53,103 --> 00:49:53,978
This...

556
00:49:55,145 --> 00:49:56,395
...perfume....

557
00:49:57,311 --> 00:49:59,436
...was highly effective....

558
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:04,020
More powerful than
I could have ever imagined.

559
00:51:28,145 --> 00:51:34,270
I have to admit, this period
was not the most unpleasant.

560
00:51:35,520 --> 00:51:36,311
Indeed.

561
00:51:36,478 --> 00:51:37,353
And then...

562
00:51:38,270 --> 00:51:41,020
...after visiting
every court in Europe...

563
00:51:41,395 --> 00:51:46,186
...I ended my journey with the famous
French court of Versailles.

564
00:51:51,436 --> 00:51:52,936
The king at the time.

565
00:51:53,145 --> 00:51:54,561
Louis, whose number...

566
00:51:55,353 --> 00:51:56,561
...I forget.

567
00:51:57,186 --> 00:51:59,603
This little Buttercup
had the bright idea...

568
00:51:59,645 --> 00:52:01,728
...to bring together all his...

569
00:52:02,020 --> 00:52:06,520
...nobles and his artists of his
kingdom to keep closer eye on them.

570
00:52:07,645 --> 00:52:10,811
There was no doubt in my mind...

571
00:52:10,977 --> 00:52:14,645
...that if Elisabeta had returned...

572
00:52:14,686 --> 00:52:16,603
...she would be here.

573
00:52:18,978 --> 00:52:21,561
I had never been
so close to finding her.

574
00:52:23,103 --> 00:52:27,145
In my heart,
I was as excited as when I began...

575
00:52:28,978 --> 00:52:30,270
- Elisabeta?
- Ah.

576
00:52:30,977 --> 00:52:34,436
Uh-uh, no, I'm not "Elizabeta"!

577
00:52:34,728 --> 00:52:35,895
I'm Isabelle de Touraine.

578
00:52:35,936 --> 00:52:38,270
But I'll change
my name if you insist.

579
00:52:50,978 --> 00:52:53,478
But my task seemed impossible...

580
00:52:53,977 --> 00:52:56,145
...and on this day,
hope left me.

581
00:53:09,770 --> 00:53:10,978
All that...

582
00:53:11,811 --> 00:53:13,936
...effort, time...

583
00:53:14,561 --> 00:53:15,977
...and money spent...

584
00:53:16,561 --> 00:53:17,977
...only served a world...

585
00:53:18,061 --> 00:53:21,978
...of debauchery and artifice,
which left no place for love.

586
00:53:37,270 --> 00:53:38,645
It was now time for me...

587
00:53:38,686 --> 00:53:42,311
...to entrust the task of finding
my Elisabeta to others.

588
00:53:44,686 --> 00:53:45,436
Uh.

589
00:54:34,436 --> 00:54:35,728
How many did you bite?

590
00:54:36,561 --> 00:54:37,977
It doesn't matter.

591
00:54:39,228 --> 00:54:42,811
Cause in the end, my associates
were as unlucky as I was.

592
00:54:44,811 --> 00:54:47,186
So I returned to my Elizabeta.

593
00:55:30,770 --> 00:55:31,728
Uh-uh.

594
00:55:51,978 --> 00:55:54,977
Since then,
I've rarely left this castle...

595
00:55:55,020 --> 00:55:58,976
...with the deluded hope that one day
my disciples will finally find...

596
00:55:58,978 --> 00:56:00,186
...my beloved.

597
00:56:08,395 --> 00:56:09,228
Mmm.

598
00:56:50,103 --> 00:56:53,020
So you seem to know what you're
talking about when it comes to love.

599
00:56:54,811 --> 00:56:55,686
I do.

600
00:56:55,977 --> 00:56:57,311
Then you have to spare me, please.

601
00:56:59,186 --> 00:57:01,895
I too have a beloved,
and you'll separate us forever!

602
00:57:02,770 --> 00:57:04,436
In whose name?
Hm?

603
00:57:04,895 --> 00:57:05,728
God?

604
00:57:08,061 --> 00:57:08,728
No...

605
00:57:10,061 --> 00:57:11,061
In the name of love.

606
00:57:15,977 --> 00:57:17,228
Are you married?

607
00:57:18,603 --> 00:57:20,061
I proposed to her,
just before I left.

608
00:57:20,228 --> 00:57:21,228
And she...

609
00:57:22,020 --> 00:57:22,811
...accepted?

610
00:57:25,311 --> 00:57:26,270
Yes, she did.

611
00:57:27,436 --> 00:57:29,270
We're to be wed
as soon as I return.

612
00:57:30,228 --> 00:57:31,895
That is unfortunate.

613
00:57:35,020 --> 00:57:37,270
If you kill me,
she'll die of grief, I know it!

614
00:57:39,270 --> 00:57:40,936
What does she look like?

615
00:57:44,186 --> 00:57:47,228
The locket,
there, around my neck.

616
00:57:47,728 --> 00:57:49,061
Inside is her photograph.

617
00:58:15,936 --> 00:58:17,895
My prince...

618
00:58:18,811 --> 00:58:19,977
My love.

619
00:58:40,895 --> 00:58:44,228
Elisa... Elisabeta!

620
00:58:45,977 --> 00:58:47,603
No... Mina.

621
00:58:48,270 --> 00:58:49,145
Mina?!

622
00:58:50,853 --> 00:58:53,977
This woman is mine, young man...

623
00:58:55,603 --> 00:58:59,811
...but I will spare your life
for finding her, for me.

624
00:59:01,311 --> 00:59:02,977
Keep him prisoner!

625
00:59:05,395 --> 00:59:07,895
I need to pack my things,
I need to...

626
00:59:08,686 --> 00:59:10,811
Everyone come down!

627
00:59:10,977 --> 00:59:12,395
Come down from there!

628
00:59:13,353 --> 00:59:15,520
Fill this vial! Fill this!

629
00:59:15,978 --> 00:59:16,977
My horses!

630
00:59:17,145 --> 00:59:18,853
Prepare my horses!

631
00:59:18,895 --> 00:59:20,103
I need to be clean!

632
00:59:20,145 --> 00:59:23,645
I need to be beautiful!
I need blood! I need blood!

633
00:59:23,728 --> 00:59:25,853
Lots of fresh blood!

634
00:59:33,520 --> 00:59:34,811
Elisabeta...

635
00:59:39,311 --> 00:59:40,436
I found you...

636
00:59:55,395 --> 00:59:56,686
This is the portrait of the woman...

637
00:59:56,770 --> 00:59:59,311
...our Prince is searching for
in your great city of Paris...

638
00:59:59,811 --> 01:00:03,103
...He's been looking for his
beloved for more than 400 years.

639
01:00:03,145 --> 01:00:05,270
We've been tracking him
for just as long...

640
01:00:05,436 --> 01:00:07,103
But the resolution...

641
01:00:07,145 --> 01:00:10,103
...of his endless wait is about
to happen now...

642
01:00:10,311 --> 01:00:12,103
...right here in the heart of Paris.

643
01:00:12,811 --> 01:00:13,853
She's left handed.

644
01:00:14,936 --> 01:00:15,853
Yeah.

645
01:00:16,020 --> 01:00:17,020
Good observation.

646
01:00:17,728 --> 01:00:20,186
This book contains
all observation...

647
01:00:20,270 --> 01:00:22,977
...my congregation has compiled
over the centuries.

648
01:00:23,311 --> 01:00:24,811
- You speak German?
- No.

649
01:00:24,978 --> 01:00:26,686
Well,
let me read you a little piece.

650
01:00:31,353 --> 01:00:34,103
It is likely that
these creatures are...

651
01:00:34,186 --> 01:00:37,561
...the way they are as
a result of a divine curse.

652
01:00:37,770 --> 01:00:39,770
Göttlich verflucht in German.

653
01:00:40,561 --> 01:00:43,353
If God can give life
then consequently...

654
01:00:43,436 --> 01:00:44,895
...he can also give death.

655
01:00:46,645 --> 01:00:48,353
But he can refuse...

656
01:00:48,895 --> 01:00:51,895
...in cases of great offense
or blasphemy.

657
01:00:51,977 --> 01:00:52,728
Ah!

658
01:00:52,811 --> 01:00:56,436
Then the offender
will be condemned...

659
01:00:56,478 --> 01:00:58,478
...to wander
the earth for all time...

660
01:00:59,353 --> 01:01:01,186
...but even more interesting...

661
01:01:01,478 --> 01:01:05,353
God can forgive
the offender, however...

662
01:01:05,853 --> 01:01:08,853
...in the event of true repentance.

663
01:01:09,436 --> 01:01:11,145
Death will be granted...

664
01:01:11,977 --> 01:01:13,770
...and the curse will be lifted.

665
01:01:13,977 --> 01:01:14,895
Ah.

666
01:01:15,686 --> 01:01:18,603
This mean, if we succeed
in destroying this demon...

667
01:01:18,645 --> 01:01:21,686
...all those who he's bitten will be
freed from the curse.

668
01:01:22,228 --> 01:01:23,353
And euh...

669
01:01:23,645 --> 01:01:25,728
Suppose we do manage
to find this demon...

670
01:01:26,020 --> 01:01:27,686
...how do you intend to
get rid of it?

671
01:01:27,728 --> 01:01:29,811
That's the easy part,
you drive a stake...

672
01:01:29,853 --> 01:01:32,103
...through his heart with a hammer
and cut off his head.

673
01:01:33,145 --> 01:01:34,020
Wonderful.

674
01:01:34,061 --> 01:01:35,395
In another book
It's mentioned that...

675
01:01:35,478 --> 01:01:37,520
...cloves of garlic
will cause it to flee...

676
01:01:37,728 --> 01:01:39,645
...I doubt this method is effective.

677
01:01:39,811 --> 01:01:41,186
Yet more within my grasp.

678
01:01:41,228 --> 01:01:42,811
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

679
01:01:42,895 --> 01:01:44,353
First, we have to find this woman.

680
01:01:44,395 --> 01:01:46,811
Because she's the only one
who can lead us to him.

681
01:01:46,895 --> 01:01:47,770
Mmhmm.

682
01:01:48,103 --> 01:01:49,270
Strange...

683
01:01:49,728 --> 01:01:50,478
What?

684
01:01:50,977 --> 01:01:52,103
The young woman in the portrait.

685
01:01:52,145 --> 01:01:53,270
Yes? What about her?

686
01:01:53,311 --> 01:01:55,228
She bears
a striking resemblance to...

687
01:01:55,436 --> 01:01:57,603
...the young woman you asked me
to keep waiting in the next room.

688
01:02:02,728 --> 01:02:03,603
Madam?

689
01:02:05,520 --> 01:02:06,895
Are you Dr. Dumont?

690
01:02:07,436 --> 01:02:09,145
Indeed, how can I help you?

691
01:02:09,395 --> 01:02:11,103
I'm a friend of Maria de Montebello.

692
01:02:11,145 --> 01:02:13,270
I learned that
she's under your care...

693
01:02:13,353 --> 01:02:15,145
...and I came to inquire
as to her condition?

694
01:02:15,436 --> 01:02:16,353
Of course.

695
01:02:18,103 --> 01:02:20,395
To... whom do I have the honour?

696
01:02:20,561 --> 01:02:22,353
Mina... Mina Murray.

697
01:02:23,645 --> 01:02:26,978
I was at Maria's wedding when...
the tragedy occurred.

698
01:02:27,436 --> 01:02:28,645
You knew her well?

699
01:02:29,270 --> 01:02:30,270
Knew?...

700
01:02:31,061 --> 01:02:31,936
...oh...

701
01:02:31,977 --> 01:02:33,853
No, no, no...
please, my apologies...

702
01:02:33,895 --> 01:02:34,811
...no, no, she's very well.

703
01:02:34,853 --> 01:02:36,228
I mean her condition is stable.

704
01:02:36,270 --> 01:02:37,103
Sorry...

705
01:02:40,645 --> 01:02:41,770
Praise be to God!

706
01:02:41,977 --> 01:02:43,395
Indeed my child.

707
01:02:46,395 --> 01:02:48,520
Would you mind if we ask
you a few questions?

708
01:02:48,561 --> 01:02:49,978
It could help her recovery.

709
01:02:50,186 --> 01:02:51,103
Yes, of course.

710
01:02:51,270 --> 01:02:52,270
Are you related?

711
01:02:52,977 --> 01:02:54,520
No, not at all.

712
01:02:55,895 --> 01:02:57,186
I am not from here.

713
01:02:57,977 --> 01:03:00,103
Can you tell us about
your relationship?

714
01:03:00,228 --> 01:03:01,103
Her behaviour?

715
01:03:01,770 --> 01:03:02,645
Ah.

716
01:03:04,145 --> 01:03:05,103
I met Maria...

717
01:03:05,853 --> 01:03:06,853
...a few days ago...

718
01:03:08,145 --> 01:03:09,145
...at a tea party...

719
01:03:10,061 --> 01:03:12,311
...that her
future husband organized.

720
01:03:13,145 --> 01:03:13,977
Henry...

721
01:03:15,977 --> 01:03:16,977
When she saw me, she...

722
01:03:17,811 --> 01:03:18,977
...she took me under her wing.

723
01:03:20,228 --> 01:03:21,686
She never really let me go.

724
01:03:24,686 --> 01:03:26,436
It was as if
she could sense that I...

725
01:03:26,728 --> 01:03:27,936
...didn't really belong.

726
01:03:29,478 --> 01:03:31,228
She took me into her room, and we...

727
01:03:32,061 --> 01:03:34,020
...we talked, we laughed a lot.

728
01:03:35,020 --> 01:03:35,977
It was so nice.

729
01:03:37,686 --> 01:03:38,977
What did you talk about?

730
01:03:39,520 --> 01:03:40,853
She could talk about anything.

731
01:03:44,353 --> 01:03:45,270
She was...

732
01:03:46,645 --> 01:03:48,728
She was particularly fond of...

733
01:03:51,728 --> 01:03:52,811
...discussing love.

734
01:03:54,895 --> 01:03:55,936
I...

735
01:03:55,977 --> 01:03:58,186
To the point of
making me uncomfortable.

736
01:04:02,145 --> 01:04:03,311
But she was so excited.

737
01:04:03,811 --> 01:04:04,977
About what exactly?

738
01:04:05,228 --> 01:04:06,270
About everything...

739
01:04:10,020 --> 01:04:10,895
And then...

740
01:04:11,853 --> 01:04:13,061
...suddenly she just...

741
01:04:15,103 --> 01:04:16,478
...she tore herself apart.

742
01:04:21,061 --> 01:04:22,228
Oh my god!

743
01:04:24,770 --> 01:04:26,353
Why did you attend that wedding?

744
01:04:27,228 --> 01:04:29,728
I...I accompanied my fiancé...

745
01:04:30,853 --> 01:04:31,811
...who knows...

746
01:04:32,478 --> 01:04:34,478
...everyone it seems.

747
01:04:35,728 --> 01:04:38,145
He's from a very respected family
I suppose.

748
01:04:38,686 --> 01:04:39,603
You suppose?

749
01:04:40,186 --> 01:04:41,228
Yes, I don't...

750
01:04:42,145 --> 01:04:43,103
I don't know.

751
01:04:48,353 --> 01:04:49,395
Get some water, please.

752
01:04:56,811 --> 01:04:57,686
My dear child...

753
01:04:57,853 --> 01:05:00,061
...you have before you
a doctor and a Priest...

754
01:05:00,145 --> 01:05:02,936
...both bound by
the strictest confidentiality.

755
01:05:03,895 --> 01:05:05,853
You can express
yourself without fear.

756
01:05:06,978 --> 01:05:09,020
To tell you the truth,
this wedding has upset me.

757
01:05:10,561 --> 01:05:12,436
Like a bad premonition.

758
01:05:13,686 --> 01:05:16,103
My engagement happened
so quickly I don't...

759
01:05:19,686 --> 01:05:20,770
I don't know if I...

760
01:05:22,061 --> 01:05:22,978
If you love him?

761
01:05:23,645 --> 01:05:24,853
I do, of course.

762
01:05:25,186 --> 01:05:26,103
He's wonderful...

763
01:05:27,145 --> 01:05:29,436
...any young woman would be
delighted by such a match.

764
01:05:29,478 --> 01:05:31,311
But you are not any young woman?

765
01:05:36,770 --> 01:05:38,270
I can't help but feel like I...

766
01:05:39,936 --> 01:05:40,811
As if I...

767
01:05:42,270 --> 01:05:43,061
As if...?

768
01:05:43,270 --> 01:05:45,020
As if I don't belong in this time...

769
01:05:51,977 --> 01:05:53,020
I apologize.

770
01:05:53,520 --> 01:05:55,478
You must think I'm
incredibly naive and...

771
01:05:56,270 --> 01:05:57,936
...I'm boring you with
my problems, I...

772
01:05:57,977 --> 01:06:00,478
Absolutely not, quite the contrary.

773
01:06:01,061 --> 01:06:03,020
Could you write down
your address, please?

774
01:06:03,353 --> 01:06:04,353
Of course.

775
01:06:04,811 --> 01:06:07,561
I'm staying at a boarding house
until Jonathan returns.

776
01:06:07,811 --> 01:06:09,228
- You're left handed?
- Yes.

777
01:06:09,353 --> 01:06:11,353
I've often been advised
to become right handed.

778
01:06:14,977 --> 01:06:15,977
Don't change a thing.

779
01:06:16,478 --> 01:06:18,020
- It's very charming.
- Well...

780
01:06:18,645 --> 01:06:20,103
Thank you for your visit.

781
01:06:20,977 --> 01:06:22,228
Thank you for seeing me.

782
01:06:23,436 --> 01:06:25,478
I'll go now to the hospital chapel
and pray for her.

783
01:06:25,561 --> 01:06:27,061
Excellent idea, my child.

784
01:06:27,645 --> 01:06:28,603
Good day.

785
01:06:44,228 --> 01:06:45,478
What is it, my son?

786
01:06:46,061 --> 01:06:48,103
I have no shelter and have...

787
01:06:48,770 --> 01:06:50,977
...not eaten for centuries.

788
01:06:51,977 --> 01:06:53,645
I am cold as well.

789
01:06:55,061 --> 01:06:56,645
I will take him to the chapel.

790
01:06:56,977 --> 01:06:58,270
Please come in.

791
01:06:58,811 --> 01:06:59,728
Come in.

792
01:06:59,977 --> 01:07:01,936
Thank you for the invitation.

793
01:07:09,103 --> 01:07:11,686
Don't move, I'll get you
a hot bowl of soup.

794
01:07:12,436 --> 01:07:13,811
You are too kind.

795
01:07:47,353 --> 01:07:48,311
Who are you?

796
01:07:48,853 --> 01:07:51,270
Count Dracula, at your service.

797
01:07:53,770 --> 01:07:55,186
Thank you for the soup...

798
01:07:55,270 --> 01:07:57,436
...but I require something richer.

799
01:08:02,728 --> 01:08:03,811
Don't worry...

800
01:08:04,520 --> 01:08:06,061
...you won't catch fire.

801
01:08:06,145 --> 01:08:08,936
Your evil spells have
no effect in the house of god!

802
01:08:09,686 --> 01:08:10,645
Oh really?

803
01:08:15,977 --> 01:08:17,686
In the name of the father...

804
01:08:18,353 --> 01:08:19,520
...the son...

805
01:08:20,395 --> 01:08:21,770
...and the evil spirit.

806
01:08:29,436 --> 01:08:31,020
Come, my sisters!

807
01:08:32,103 --> 01:08:34,311
Look what God has made of you.

808
01:08:34,977 --> 01:08:38,478
Hearts of stone in dormant bodies...

809
01:08:39,478 --> 01:08:43,353
...suffocating under
their own thick issue.

810
01:08:46,103 --> 01:08:48,561
Let me free you from this prison!

811
01:09:01,061 --> 01:09:02,145
No!

812
01:09:12,936 --> 01:09:13,936
Come on!!!

813
01:10:21,895 --> 01:10:23,103
Hey!

814
01:10:37,186 --> 01:10:38,061
Ah.

815
01:13:05,311 --> 01:13:06,395
Ah!

816
01:14:28,645 --> 01:14:29,853
Ah! Ah!

817
01:15:00,770 --> 01:15:02,145
Master!

818
01:15:08,561 --> 01:15:09,561
Good evening?

819
01:15:11,145 --> 01:15:12,520
The hospital is closed.

820
01:15:27,895 --> 01:15:29,770
I found her Master!

821
01:15:29,811 --> 01:15:31,353
I found her!

822
01:15:32,353 --> 01:15:33,478
You've done very well.

823
01:15:33,561 --> 01:15:36,020
Oh. Thank you, thank you.

824
01:15:36,186 --> 01:15:37,520
You deserve a reward.

825
01:15:45,603 --> 01:15:50,645
Oh, come, come, my little boy...

826
01:15:55,353 --> 01:15:56,936
Come closer.

827
01:16:14,895 --> 01:16:16,520
Here you are...

828
01:16:21,228 --> 01:16:22,603
Sorry for disturbing you Father...

829
01:16:22,895 --> 01:16:24,478
...but doctor Dumont needs
to see you immediately.

830
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:25,645
Yeah... I'm coming.

831
01:16:26,478 --> 01:16:28,186
If this patient's disappearance...

832
01:16:28,228 --> 01:16:29,686
...could remain
a secret between us...

833
01:16:29,728 --> 01:16:30,853
...at least for a while?

834
01:16:31,270 --> 01:16:32,561
You can count on me.

835
01:16:34,478 --> 01:16:35,311
Here.

836
01:16:36,811 --> 01:16:38,270
- Allez.
- Monsieur.

837
01:16:38,353 --> 01:16:39,186
Hey!

838
01:16:44,395 --> 01:16:45,645
He lost a lot of blood.

839
01:16:45,728 --> 01:16:47,770
I was thinking of giving
a transfusion.

840
01:16:47,977 --> 01:16:49,478
I'm sure he would have loved that.

841
01:16:49,520 --> 01:16:51,186
Oh... Yes, of course, sorry.

842
01:16:52,020 --> 01:16:54,020
He uses a pleasant perfume.

843
01:16:54,228 --> 01:16:55,145
I never noticed.

844
01:16:55,395 --> 01:16:57,311
How could she have escaped
with all the chains?

845
01:16:57,395 --> 01:16:58,770
There was an outside accomplice.

846
01:16:58,936 --> 01:16:59,728
A man...

847
01:16:59,895 --> 01:17:01,353
He was seen wandering the hospital.

848
01:17:01,561 --> 01:17:02,853
- Is there a description?
- Mm.

849
01:17:03,603 --> 01:17:04,436
Thirties.

850
01:17:04,520 --> 01:17:05,978
Elegant and richly dressed.

851
01:17:06,395 --> 01:17:08,395
Blue eyes. Tall and upright.

852
01:17:08,978 --> 01:17:10,103
Mina is in danger.

853
01:17:10,561 --> 01:17:11,561
We must warn her.

854
01:17:22,478 --> 01:17:23,895
Are you cold my child?

855
01:17:24,811 --> 01:17:25,603
No...

856
01:17:26,811 --> 01:17:28,978
I've always loved
the spectacle of fire.

857
01:17:30,561 --> 01:17:31,853
Expecting visitors?

858
01:17:32,145 --> 01:17:33,020
No.

859
01:17:33,478 --> 01:17:34,520
I'll see what it's about.

860
01:17:39,645 --> 01:17:40,436
Tada!

861
01:17:40,520 --> 01:17:42,311
Maria?!!

862
01:17:42,895 --> 01:17:44,853
- But... You're cured?
- Indeed I am!

863
01:17:45,186 --> 01:17:46,811
Oh, It's a miracle! I'm so...

864
01:17:47,061 --> 01:17:48,478
- ...I'm so relieved!!
- Don't worry.

865
01:17:48,520 --> 01:17:51,436
Evil is gone as quickly as it came.

866
01:17:51,811 --> 01:17:53,603
Let's not speak of it anymore.

867
01:17:53,645 --> 01:17:56,520
- But you're feeling...
- In tip-top shape!

868
01:17:56,561 --> 01:17:59,520
And ready to celebrate
my return in grand style.

869
01:17:59,603 --> 01:18:01,395
- Dr. Dumont - he let you go?
- Well...

870
01:18:01,645 --> 01:18:02,978
I have so much energy today...

871
01:18:03,061 --> 01:18:04,228
...I don't think he could
have stopped me!

872
01:18:05,436 --> 01:18:07,436
- And your fiancé?
- In Scotland!

873
01:18:07,478 --> 01:18:08,978
Oh! Look what I have.

874
01:18:10,270 --> 01:18:12,603
- Put your hat! We'll go together!
- Where?

875
01:18:12,686 --> 01:18:15,020
Three front-row tickets for
today's celebration!

876
01:18:15,061 --> 01:18:15,978
You're welcome.

877
01:18:16,186 --> 01:18:17,936
- Three?
- Oh yes, my friend...

878
01:18:17,977 --> 01:18:19,977
...the one I've been telling you
about is in town...

879
01:18:20,228 --> 01:18:22,186
...and he is dying to meet you.

880
01:18:22,895 --> 01:18:24,061
Quickly go change...

881
01:18:24,228 --> 01:18:25,145
Go change!

882
01:18:29,936 --> 01:18:30,853
Ah!

883
01:18:41,853 --> 01:18:43,311
- Bonjour!
- Bienvenue, bonjour.

884
01:18:43,977 --> 01:18:46,603
- Where are you taking me?
- At the Grand Hotel.

885
01:18:47,103 --> 01:18:49,895
They serve wonderful hot chocolate,
you have to try it.

886
01:18:57,145 --> 01:18:57,977
Ah!

887
01:19:30,186 --> 01:19:31,061
Where have you been?

888
01:19:31,228 --> 01:19:33,311
Ciao Maurice.

889
01:19:42,977 --> 01:19:45,061
Well, I know my friend is
very beautiful...

890
01:19:45,103 --> 01:19:46,228
...but I'm a bit offended!

891
01:19:47,186 --> 01:19:47,977
Forgive me...

892
01:19:49,936 --> 01:19:52,020
...your beauty brings light
to this place...

893
01:19:52,478 --> 01:19:54,395
...filled with dark suits
and top hats.

894
01:19:56,811 --> 01:19:57,561
Very true!

895
01:19:57,603 --> 01:19:59,561
Madam, it is an honour...

896
01:20:01,061 --> 01:20:02,936
...and a pleasure to see you again.

897
01:20:03,436 --> 01:20:04,395
Have we met before?

898
01:20:05,103 --> 01:20:06,436
In a dream, perhaps.

899
01:20:07,895 --> 01:20:09,603
I have the strange feeling...

900
01:20:09,728 --> 01:20:11,270
...that we have known each other...

901
01:20:12,353 --> 01:20:13,436
...for a long time.

902
01:20:13,853 --> 01:20:16,186
That's very romantic.

903
01:20:16,270 --> 01:20:17,103
Terribly.

904
01:20:20,478 --> 01:20:21,520
Excuse me.

905
01:20:21,895 --> 01:20:25,853
I seem to have lost my mind
and my manners.

906
01:20:26,645 --> 01:20:28,895
Vlad the second,
Prince of Wallachia...

907
01:20:29,977 --> 01:20:31,020
Count Dracula

908
01:20:37,353 --> 01:20:38,520
It's a pleasure to meet you.

909
01:20:39,478 --> 01:20:40,395
Maria?

910
01:20:41,228 --> 01:20:42,978
You promised me hot chocolate.

911
01:20:43,145 --> 01:20:45,686
Yes, but first we're
going to have a little fun!

912
01:20:45,770 --> 01:20:46,645
- Mm?
- Mm.

913
01:20:46,686 --> 01:20:47,603
Mm.

914
01:20:48,686 --> 01:20:49,520
Sorry!

915
01:21:10,228 --> 01:21:11,228
I am sorry.

916
01:21:31,686 --> 01:21:32,977
Oh!

917
01:21:34,270 --> 01:21:35,228
Oh!

918
01:21:38,061 --> 01:21:39,603
Un... Deux... Trois...

919
01:21:50,145 --> 01:21:51,020
Oh, let's go.

920
01:21:57,811 --> 01:21:59,353
Allez-y mademoiselle. Un...

921
01:22:01,895 --> 01:22:03,728
Bravo, bravo! Murray.

922
01:22:05,436 --> 01:22:06,228
Ouh!

923
01:22:08,311 --> 01:22:10,561
All right, lets go!
Oh, look at that!

924
01:22:11,103 --> 01:22:12,977
I want to see the exhibition.

925
01:22:14,603 --> 01:22:15,770
Chicken Lady!

926
01:22:16,103 --> 01:22:18,103
Oh my god, it's so beautiful,
look at that.

927
01:22:18,270 --> 01:22:19,977
Oh, wow.

928
01:22:20,395 --> 01:22:21,728
The old lady with the beard!

929
01:22:22,436 --> 01:22:24,228
Hello.

930
01:22:24,311 --> 01:22:25,186
Beautiful!

931
01:22:25,728 --> 01:22:26,811
Look at that.

932
01:22:35,353 --> 01:22:36,311
Mina!

933
01:22:36,395 --> 01:22:37,686
Come! Come!

934
01:22:41,853 --> 01:22:44,686
- You see Mina? It's beautiful.
- Ladies and gentleman...

935
01:22:44,728 --> 01:22:46,186
A little quiet please!

936
01:22:46,228 --> 01:22:48,311
I'm going to feed the beast!

937
01:23:04,020 --> 01:23:06,145
She is beautiful.

938
01:23:20,311 --> 01:23:22,145
The Little animal.

939
01:23:25,311 --> 01:23:27,478
- Oh, this is scary Mina!
- No, no, no, no.

940
01:23:27,561 --> 01:23:28,895
Yeah, let's go!

941
01:23:35,561 --> 01:23:36,520
Maria?

942
01:23:37,478 --> 01:23:38,436
Maria!

943
01:23:43,270 --> 01:23:44,395
This way.

944
01:23:46,770 --> 01:23:48,103
That girl wants to shoot!

945
01:24:08,895 --> 01:24:10,145
Bravo, Mina!

946
01:24:15,853 --> 01:24:17,811
Allez, allez, monsieur!

947
01:24:19,311 --> 01:24:20,436
Allez!

948
01:24:22,936 --> 01:24:24,228
Allez!

949
01:24:30,395 --> 01:24:33,270
I took the liberty to
have libations prepared...

950
01:24:33,311 --> 01:24:34,811
...while we wait for tonight show.

951
01:24:34,895 --> 01:24:35,977
Excellent!

952
01:24:36,145 --> 01:24:37,728
Maria, It's not really
proper to visit...

953
01:24:37,811 --> 01:24:39,436
...the room of a man
we've only just met?

954
01:24:39,478 --> 01:24:41,145
Don't worry,
I won't let go of your arm.

955
01:24:43,770 --> 01:24:44,936
Tada!

956
01:24:46,977 --> 01:24:47,853
What do you think?

957
01:24:48,270 --> 01:24:49,270
It's wonderful.

958
01:24:49,895 --> 01:24:51,895
I don't know about you,
but I'm starving.

959
01:24:54,103 --> 01:24:55,311
I'm exhausted.

960
01:24:55,853 --> 01:24:56,853
All right, all right.

961
01:24:57,061 --> 01:24:59,270
Oh, you sit here, princess...

962
01:25:00,103 --> 01:25:01,936
...and I'll bring you
a hot chocolate.

963
01:25:09,936 --> 01:25:10,853
Ah!

964
01:25:14,895 --> 01:25:15,561
Oh!

965
01:25:15,645 --> 01:25:17,853
Thank you for accepting
my invitation.

966
01:25:19,645 --> 01:25:21,603
Your apartment is fit for a king.

967
01:25:21,770 --> 01:25:22,936
I'm just a prince.

968
01:25:23,977 --> 01:25:25,978
- Sorry...
- Do you live in Paris?

969
01:25:26,645 --> 01:25:28,270
No, further north.

970
01:25:28,311 --> 01:25:30,853
In the country,
where life is quieter.

971
01:25:31,478 --> 01:25:33,561
- You like the quiet?
- Not at all.

972
01:25:34,228 --> 01:25:35,811
I love nature...

973
01:25:36,811 --> 01:25:38,853
...birds, trees...

974
01:25:39,645 --> 01:25:41,436
...and the wind that
makes them sing.

975
01:25:46,895 --> 01:25:48,478
May I ask, where do you live?

976
01:25:48,645 --> 01:25:50,728
My family home is an old castle...

977
01:25:52,020 --> 01:25:54,561
...at the foot of
the Carpathian Mountains...

978
01:25:54,770 --> 01:25:56,353
...in Romania.

979
01:25:57,311 --> 01:25:59,895
There I know
only winter and loneliness.

980
01:26:00,770 --> 01:26:01,811
I love winter.

981
01:26:02,978 --> 01:26:04,478
With its harsh landscapes.

982
01:26:05,436 --> 01:26:07,520
But my parents dream of Andalusia.

983
01:26:09,645 --> 01:26:11,895
Perhaps the memory of another...

984
01:26:12,645 --> 01:26:13,936
...older life.

985
01:26:16,353 --> 01:26:17,561
I suppose so.

986
01:26:21,686 --> 01:26:22,936
May I show you something?

987
01:26:24,977 --> 01:26:25,895
Yes.

988
01:26:44,811 --> 01:26:45,977
It's beautiful...

989
01:26:46,895 --> 01:26:47,936
...what is it?

990
01:26:48,311 --> 01:26:49,645
It is a music box.

991
01:26:50,561 --> 01:26:52,686
Many people think
it was invented in the...

992
01:26:52,770 --> 01:26:54,770
...18th century by the Swiss.

993
01:26:54,811 --> 01:26:56,311
But I found this one...

994
01:26:56,478 --> 01:26:59,270
...at a merchant's table
in Constantinople.

995
01:27:00,395 --> 01:27:02,353
It dates from the 15th century.

996
01:27:03,228 --> 01:27:04,103
Remarkable.

997
01:27:05,811 --> 01:27:07,770
I gave it to my wife as a gift.

998
01:27:09,270 --> 01:27:10,436
You're married?

999
01:27:12,561 --> 01:27:13,478
Widowed.

1000
01:27:14,353 --> 01:27:15,977
- Forgive me.
- You're forgiven.

1001
01:27:18,186 --> 01:27:19,478
And it still works?

1002
01:27:19,520 --> 01:27:20,770
Of course.

1003
01:27:34,645 --> 01:27:36,186
Do you know this melody?

1004
01:27:45,061 --> 01:27:46,270
It seems so familiar...

1005
01:27:50,895 --> 01:27:52,353
But I trace my memory.

1006
01:27:54,103 --> 01:27:55,853
I don't know from where...or when...

1007
01:27:56,020 --> 01:27:57,395
Keep searching...

1008
01:28:04,645 --> 01:28:06,603
In your heart... In your skin...

1009
01:28:07,103 --> 01:28:09,561
In your soul...

1010
01:28:11,103 --> 01:28:13,186
Do you feel me... Elisabeta...

1011
01:28:16,770 --> 01:28:18,395
What kind of spell are
you putting on me?

1012
01:28:18,478 --> 01:28:19,645
None, Mina.

1013
01:28:20,645 --> 01:28:23,228
I'm only haunted
by the memory of my wife...

1014
01:28:23,478 --> 01:28:26,603
...my one and only love and
you look so much like her that...

1015
01:28:27,103 --> 01:28:28,186
...it troubles me.

1016
01:28:29,478 --> 01:28:31,436
Her name was Elisabeta...

1017
01:28:31,936 --> 01:28:33,103
...and when she wanted me...

1018
01:28:33,977 --> 01:28:35,561
...she used to play
this little tune...

1019
01:28:35,603 --> 01:28:37,228
...that echoed through the castle.

1020
01:28:38,645 --> 01:28:40,728
It was my signal to run to her.

1021
01:28:40,977 --> 01:28:42,436
This is all very touching...

1022
01:28:44,395 --> 01:28:45,561
I am Mina.

1023
01:28:46,686 --> 01:28:47,603
Mina Murray...

1024
01:28:47,645 --> 01:28:48,728
...and I am getting married in...

1025
01:28:48,811 --> 01:28:50,436
- ...a few weeks time.
- Yes, of course.

1026
01:28:50,811 --> 01:28:53,186
Forgive me for bothering you
with my stories.

1027
01:28:54,020 --> 01:28:55,520
These are old pains that...

1028
01:28:56,020 --> 01:28:58,145
...your presence has
brought back to life.

1029
01:28:59,728 --> 01:29:02,061
And I sincerely apologize for this.

1030
01:29:03,686 --> 01:29:04,686
Please...

1031
01:29:05,936 --> 01:29:08,228
Sir, I cannot accept this.
This is far too precious.

1032
01:29:08,311 --> 01:29:10,395
A gift can never be refused.

1033
01:29:11,311 --> 01:29:14,228
And maybe this melody
brings back some memories.

1034
01:29:14,977 --> 01:29:16,353
Mina! Come!

1035
01:29:16,520 --> 01:29:18,103
It's gonna start in ten seconds...

1036
01:29:18,686 --> 01:29:21,186
...now you have to come, let's go!

1037
01:29:24,145 --> 01:29:27,978
3...2...1!!

1038
01:29:32,228 --> 01:29:33,728
Oh, my God!

1039
01:29:52,145 --> 01:29:53,020
It's here.

1040
01:29:54,561 --> 01:29:55,936
Thank you for the wonderful evening.

1041
01:29:56,478 --> 01:29:59,853
It is been an eternity since
I have known such...

1042
01:30:02,311 --> 01:30:03,311
happiness.

1043
01:30:03,853 --> 01:30:05,603
Has the word become
unfamiliar to you?

1044
01:30:07,228 --> 01:30:08,728
My wife took it with her.

1045
01:30:13,686 --> 01:30:14,645
Good night then.

1046
01:30:21,770 --> 01:30:22,645
Good night.

1047
01:30:44,645 --> 01:30:46,520
Jonathan?! Jonathan!

1048
01:30:46,603 --> 01:30:47,853
What is happening to you?!

1049
01:30:47,936 --> 01:30:49,436
I thought
I will never see you again.

1050
01:30:49,478 --> 01:30:51,977
Please, please, It's better he rest.

1051
01:30:52,020 --> 01:30:52,977
He's worn out.

1052
01:30:53,020 --> 01:30:54,228
What's happened to him?

1053
01:30:55,270 --> 01:30:56,311
- Mina?
- Oh father.

1054
01:30:56,520 --> 01:30:57,728
Do you know where he went?

1055
01:30:58,228 --> 01:30:59,895
No. Not exactly.

1056
01:30:59,936 --> 01:31:02,686
To a castle where
he was held prisoner...

1057
01:31:03,061 --> 01:31:05,977
...and from which he was
miraculously able to escape...

1058
01:31:06,020 --> 01:31:07,353
...at the risk of his very life.

1059
01:31:07,436 --> 01:31:09,353
And do you know
who owns this castle?

1060
01:31:10,895 --> 01:31:11,686
No.

1061
01:31:11,770 --> 01:31:14,103
Maria's very good friend,
Count Dracula...

1062
01:31:14,186 --> 01:31:16,228
...the one who's infected her
and many others.

1063
01:31:16,311 --> 01:31:17,145
What?

1064
01:31:17,603 --> 01:31:19,270
No... no you m...

1065
01:31:19,603 --> 01:31:21,186
You must be mistaken. The count...

1066
01:31:21,811 --> 01:31:23,811
The Count is charming... and he...

1067
01:31:25,270 --> 01:31:26,186
You've met him.

1068
01:31:26,353 --> 01:31:27,353
Yes, the count...

1069
01:31:29,186 --> 01:31:30,603
He's an absolute gentleman...

1070
01:31:30,686 --> 01:31:32,395
...he even walked
me to my door, he's...

1071
01:31:35,395 --> 01:31:36,645
...I don't understand.

1072
01:31:43,728 --> 01:31:44,895
How did he find you?

1073
01:31:44,936 --> 01:31:45,895
I don't know.

1074
01:31:46,436 --> 01:31:47,686
It's all happened so quickly.

1075
01:31:47,728 --> 01:31:49,311
Maria came here...

1076
01:31:49,977 --> 01:31:51,770
...and she told me
you'd released her.

1077
01:31:52,061 --> 01:31:54,728
Maria escaped, knocking out
three guards in the process...

1078
01:31:54,977 --> 01:31:57,061
...and drained most of
the blood from my clerk.

1079
01:31:57,145 --> 01:31:57,977
What?

1080
01:31:58,020 --> 01:32:00,645
I... I don't believe it, she...

1081
01:32:00,686 --> 01:32:01,728
Take a seat...

1082
01:32:03,311 --> 01:32:04,603
...and calm yourself...

1083
01:32:05,020 --> 01:32:06,978
...because what
I am about to tell you...

1084
01:32:07,061 --> 01:32:08,770
...will be difficult to hear...

1085
01:32:09,520 --> 01:32:11,520
...and even more so to understand.

1086
01:32:14,728 --> 01:32:16,603
That man is a hematophagous.

1087
01:32:17,977 --> 01:32:20,561
It feeds exclusively on fresh blood.

1088
01:32:20,770 --> 01:32:22,061
Human blood mostly.

1089
01:32:24,061 --> 01:32:25,228
He's a vampire.

1090
01:32:28,311 --> 01:32:29,645
Yes. He is.

1091
01:32:30,103 --> 01:32:32,436
It bites its victims,
usually in the neck...

1092
01:32:32,478 --> 01:32:34,895
...and sucks their blood
until they're dead.

1093
01:32:35,395 --> 01:32:37,103
Some of them are, sort to say...

1094
01:32:37,186 --> 01:32:39,686
...spared, but they become
vampires themselves.

1095
01:32:39,728 --> 01:32:40,645
Oh my God!

1096
01:32:41,020 --> 01:32:42,228
Maria is one of them.

1097
01:32:42,270 --> 01:32:44,395
I need to make sure
that you're not as well.

1098
01:32:45,311 --> 01:32:47,395
Maria... of course not.

1099
01:32:47,436 --> 01:32:48,853
He never touched or
disrespected me...

1100
01:32:48,895 --> 01:32:50,561
...he behaved like
a perfect gentleman.

1101
01:32:52,145 --> 01:32:55,395
He uses a perfume
to seduce his victims...

1102
01:32:55,436 --> 01:32:57,186
...a kind of elixir
that annihilates...

1103
01:32:57,228 --> 01:32:58,977
...all will and removes
all inhibition.

1104
01:32:59,436 --> 01:33:02,103
So you may be under his spell
and not even know it.

1105
01:33:03,686 --> 01:33:04,728
How awful.

1106
01:33:05,061 --> 01:33:06,728
Yeah... Indeed.

1107
01:33:07,436 --> 01:33:08,936
But it's easy to verify.

1108
01:33:10,228 --> 01:33:11,811
May I see your neck please?

1109
01:33:25,395 --> 01:33:26,478
Ah!

1110
01:33:27,270 --> 01:33:28,270
All is well.

1111
01:33:28,770 --> 01:33:30,228
It's a miracle really.

1112
01:33:31,478 --> 01:33:32,395
Please.

1113
01:33:33,228 --> 01:33:34,478
Please. Please.

1114
01:33:44,436 --> 01:33:45,478
- This way.
- Ah!

1115
01:33:46,895 --> 01:33:48,395
Good evening sir! Father.

1116
01:34:01,186 --> 01:34:01,976
Easy.

1117
01:34:01,978 --> 01:34:02,895
Quiet, please.

1118
01:34:02,977 --> 01:34:04,936
- We have guests who are sleeping.
- Yes. Sorry, sorry...

1119
01:35:09,186 --> 01:35:10,061
What are you doing?

1120
01:35:10,103 --> 01:35:11,645
Don't take another
step or I'll scream!

1121
01:35:11,728 --> 01:35:13,853
Mina. Don't be afraid.
I mean you no harm.

1122
01:35:14,520 --> 01:35:16,728
- Yes?
- Miss, I seem to remember being...

1123
01:35:16,770 --> 01:35:18,686
...perfectly clear about
the rules of the house...

1124
01:35:18,728 --> 01:35:20,770
...which include no music after 8pm.

1125
01:35:20,811 --> 01:35:21,977
And it's past midnight.

1126
01:35:22,020 --> 01:35:23,978
Please forgive me,
I hadn't noticed the time.

1127
01:35:24,061 --> 01:35:24,936
Good.

1128
01:35:26,103 --> 01:35:27,020
Now, sir...

1129
01:35:27,645 --> 01:35:28,976
...if you are the gentleman
you claim to be...

1130
01:35:28,978 --> 01:35:30,520
...you leave this room immediately.

1131
01:35:30,686 --> 01:35:33,228
I understand. My regards.

1132
01:35:33,686 --> 01:35:35,103
No! Not that way!

1133
01:35:35,311 --> 01:35:36,228
Go out the way you came.

1134
01:35:42,061 --> 01:35:43,186
What are you doing?

1135
01:35:43,895 --> 01:35:45,645
What are you doing?
What are you doing?

1136
01:35:45,895 --> 01:35:47,436
You can't jump - it's much too high!

1137
01:35:47,478 --> 01:35:51,020
Mina, I've waited almost
four hundred years to see you again.

1138
01:35:51,103 --> 01:35:52,978
So if you want me to leave, I can.

1139
01:35:53,061 --> 01:35:54,603
Yes... Now, leave!

1140
01:35:56,103 --> 01:35:59,020
No, I forbid you from killing
yourself under my window!

1141
01:35:59,603 --> 01:36:01,686
So you'd like me to
die further away?

1142
01:36:01,728 --> 01:36:03,811
Yes! No! YES!

1143
01:36:04,436 --> 01:36:06,895
Just get off the
balcony immediately!

1144
01:36:14,228 --> 01:36:15,228
You lied to me!

1145
01:36:15,811 --> 01:36:17,020
Not even once.

1146
01:36:17,061 --> 01:36:19,895
You use charm to seduce me,
like you do to all your victims.

1147
01:36:20,020 --> 01:36:21,103
You are right...

1148
01:36:21,686 --> 01:36:22,895
...it is a perfume.

1149
01:36:23,520 --> 01:36:25,145
But I never used it with you.

1150
01:36:27,478 --> 01:36:29,311
I'm told you drink
the blood of your victims?!

1151
01:36:29,520 --> 01:36:31,686
It's true,
but you are not my victim...

1152
01:36:31,811 --> 01:36:33,270
- ...you're my beloved.
- Quiet!

1153
01:36:33,311 --> 01:36:35,145
My one and only true love.

1154
01:36:35,770 --> 01:36:37,728
Who are you to talk
to me like that?!

1155
01:36:37,770 --> 01:36:39,311
I'm damned, Mina.

1156
01:36:40,145 --> 01:36:42,728
I'm a dead man condemned
by God's will to live.

1157
01:36:44,478 --> 01:36:45,977
Why would God do such a thing?

1158
01:36:46,728 --> 01:36:48,186
Because he took you from me...

1159
01:36:50,103 --> 01:36:52,270
...so I cursed him and
abandoned him.

1160
01:36:52,353 --> 01:36:55,603
And, contrary to popular belief,
I don't like blood.

1161
01:36:56,520 --> 01:36:58,895
Even if yours has
a delicious taste to it.

1162
01:37:01,811 --> 01:37:05,020
Without it, I would only be
a repulsive old man...

1163
01:37:05,103 --> 01:37:07,353
...whom you'd hardly
deign to look at.

1164
01:37:07,436 --> 01:37:08,936
These are all just words.

1165
01:37:10,436 --> 01:37:12,811
Charming words meant to deceive me!

1166
01:37:12,977 --> 01:37:15,186
You're right, sometimes words
can deceive.

1167
01:37:15,436 --> 01:37:16,478
Take my hands.

1168
01:37:18,186 --> 01:37:19,645
Hands never lie.

1169
01:37:20,770 --> 01:37:23,228
I will tell you the
truth about me...

1170
01:37:23,270 --> 01:37:24,478
...but also about you.

1171
01:37:24,811 --> 01:37:26,686
About who you really are.

1172
01:37:27,977 --> 01:37:29,561
They will tell you...

1173
01:37:29,977 --> 01:37:31,561
...how much they enjoyed...

1174
01:37:32,561 --> 01:37:34,311
...caressing your face...

1175
01:37:34,395 --> 01:37:36,853
...and your neck and your hips too.

1176
01:37:39,977 --> 01:37:41,978
Remember the last thing
you said to me?

1177
01:37:44,061 --> 01:37:46,811
You said: take care of yourself
my prince...

1178
01:37:47,561 --> 01:37:48,645
...my king.

1179
01:37:49,270 --> 01:37:50,186
My life.

1180
01:37:53,686 --> 01:37:56,645
Because
I cannot survive without you.

1181
01:38:00,270 --> 01:38:01,603
Oh my love.

1182
01:38:14,603 --> 01:38:16,311
I missed you so much.

1183
01:38:16,936 --> 01:38:18,311
I missed you too.

1184
01:38:20,436 --> 01:38:22,770
I want to be with you forever now.

1185
01:38:24,561 --> 01:38:26,770
- Take me.
- I cannot.

1186
01:38:28,228 --> 01:38:29,020
Why?

1187
01:38:29,103 --> 01:38:30,103
Take me...

1188
01:38:30,603 --> 01:38:31,977
I want you to take me!

1189
01:38:32,395 --> 01:38:33,228
Now!

1190
01:38:33,395 --> 01:38:35,645
You have your all life ahead of you.

1191
01:38:36,770 --> 01:38:38,436
And I only offer death.

1192
01:38:40,561 --> 01:38:42,770
I want to be your flesh...

1193
01:38:43,395 --> 01:38:44,561
...and your blood.

1194
01:38:47,270 --> 01:38:48,270
Please.

1195
01:38:49,561 --> 01:38:50,977
Please, my husband.

1196
01:38:52,186 --> 01:38:53,103
Please.

1197
01:39:21,186 --> 01:39:22,061
Dumont?

1198
01:39:22,395 --> 01:39:23,603
- Yes?
- That smell?

1199
01:39:25,145 --> 01:39:26,770
It's the same as in the hospital!

1200
01:39:27,728 --> 01:39:28,895
Same perfume.

1201
01:39:32,145 --> 01:39:33,103
He's here.

1202
01:39:33,977 --> 01:39:34,977
Oh my God!

1203
01:39:47,728 --> 01:39:48,603
They're left.

1204
01:39:49,103 --> 01:39:50,145
But where?

1205
01:39:52,020 --> 01:39:53,353
There's only one place.

1206
01:39:57,395 --> 01:39:59,603
It appears Mina's gone missing.

1207
01:40:00,186 --> 01:40:02,061
- With him?
- I'm afraid so.

1208
01:40:04,895 --> 01:40:05,977
This man is the devil.

1209
01:40:06,811 --> 01:40:08,603
He must be stopped
as soon as possible!

1210
01:40:08,728 --> 01:40:09,603
Precisely.

1211
01:40:09,936 --> 01:40:11,895
But do you think
you'll be able to guide us...

1212
01:40:11,977 --> 01:40:13,895
- ...to his castle in Romania?
- Yes.

1213
01:40:13,977 --> 01:40:15,561
Father?
We can't just go like that...

1214
01:40:15,603 --> 01:40:17,603
...without any preparation,
without any help!

1215
01:40:20,145 --> 01:40:22,145
I think I know someone
who could help us.

1216
01:40:36,228 --> 01:40:37,353
Ta-da!

1217
01:40:38,270 --> 01:40:40,561
Henry William, amore mio!

1218
01:40:41,728 --> 01:40:43,270
So you missed me?

1219
01:40:43,311 --> 01:40:44,728
Of course, my darling!

1220
01:40:44,770 --> 01:40:46,478
I prayed for you every day, but...

1221
01:40:46,728 --> 01:40:48,686
- what happened? Is this a miracle?
- It is!

1222
01:40:49,520 --> 01:40:51,103
God heard your prayers.

1223
01:40:51,395 --> 01:40:53,353
And here I am,
completely healed and...

1224
01:40:53,436 --> 01:40:55,311
...ready to love you for
the rest of your life!

1225
01:40:56,728 --> 01:40:57,561
Henry...

1226
01:40:58,228 --> 01:41:01,228
...I was going mad without you.

1227
01:41:01,728 --> 01:41:03,436
When were you discharged
from the hospital?

1228
01:41:03,478 --> 01:41:05,020
I...
I asked them to let me know as...

1229
01:41:05,103 --> 01:41:06,228
I know, I know.

1230
01:41:06,561 --> 01:41:09,145
I left barely an hour ago and
came straight here.

1231
01:41:09,228 --> 01:41:11,478
- And... Are you completely cured?
- Of course!

1232
01:41:11,895 --> 01:41:13,936
Don't bore me with your questions.

1233
01:41:14,353 --> 01:41:15,811
Aren't you excited to see me?

1234
01:41:16,061 --> 01:41:17,977
Of course.

1235
01:41:20,186 --> 01:41:21,145
Oh Henry.

1236
01:41:21,561 --> 01:41:23,020
I missed your arms...

1237
01:41:23,603 --> 01:41:25,936
...and these beautiful hands...

1238
01:41:26,478 --> 01:41:27,853
and your lips!

1239
01:41:29,311 --> 01:41:31,353
Especially your neck.

1240
01:41:40,353 --> 01:41:41,228
Maria!

1241
01:41:42,436 --> 01:41:44,395
How dare you?!

1242
01:41:50,228 --> 01:41:52,686
Jes.. Jesus! What did you do?!

1243
01:41:52,936 --> 01:41:55,728
Do not worry, do not worry,
there is an explanation.

1244
01:41:55,811 --> 01:41:57,311
We can explain everything.

1245
01:41:59,895 --> 01:42:01,311
Oh no my blood!

1246
01:42:01,561 --> 01:42:03,186
Oh... what have you done?

1247
01:42:03,645 --> 01:42:04,978
Look what you've done!

1248
01:42:05,353 --> 01:42:08,353
Oh, it's all over the carpet!

1249
01:42:08,520 --> 01:42:10,353
What have you done?!

1250
01:42:11,311 --> 01:42:12,770
- My darling, don'...
- Oh, shut up, Henry!

1251
01:42:12,853 --> 01:42:13,603
My dear...

1252
01:42:20,561 --> 01:42:21,561
Help!

1253
01:42:22,478 --> 01:42:23,770
Maria.

1254
01:42:24,478 --> 01:42:26,186
Don'... Don't... Aaaah!

1255
01:42:26,228 --> 01:42:27,311
No, no!

1256
01:43:54,145 --> 01:43:55,478
Welcome home.

1257
01:44:03,770 --> 01:44:04,728
My friends.

1258
01:44:06,103 --> 01:44:08,561
Princess Elizabeta has returned.

1259
01:44:41,311 --> 01:44:42,770
Let me talk to them.

1260
01:44:43,311 --> 01:44:44,520
I won't be long.

1261
01:44:54,977 --> 01:44:55,895
Master!

1262
01:44:57,145 --> 01:44:58,603
They are already on your trail...

1263
01:44:58,853 --> 01:45:00,686
...and will surely find you soon.

1264
01:45:01,020 --> 01:45:02,686
I think it is time for you to leave.

1265
01:45:03,686 --> 01:45:05,478
Thank you for your concern.

1266
01:45:06,728 --> 01:45:08,395
But we are finally at home.

1267
01:45:09,478 --> 01:45:10,811
There is nowhere else to be.

1268
01:45:55,811 --> 01:45:56,853
Take this.

1269
01:45:58,436 --> 01:46:01,145
I don't think I will need
your services anymore.

1270
01:46:01,978 --> 01:46:03,145
Go in peace now.

1271
01:47:31,936 --> 01:47:33,186
Elizabeta.

1272
01:47:33,728 --> 01:47:34,686
My prince.

1273
01:47:37,270 --> 01:47:38,728
Do you think God will forgive us...

1274
01:47:38,811 --> 01:47:40,603
...for loving each other so much?

1275
01:47:41,061 --> 01:47:42,811
God is love.

1276
01:47:44,186 --> 01:47:45,395
He understands.

1277
01:47:48,186 --> 01:47:49,770
And if he doesn't...

1278
01:47:50,853 --> 01:47:51,936
...he can go to hell.

1279
01:48:20,895 --> 01:48:23,436
They will know what it is
to wake a dragon.

1280
01:48:23,603 --> 01:48:24,603
Stay here.

1281
01:49:35,020 --> 01:49:35,853
Over there.

1282
01:49:35,895 --> 01:49:37,186
That's where he
sleeps in his coffin.

1283
01:49:37,228 --> 01:49:38,978
A coffin? That's the last place
I want to sleep.

1284
01:49:39,061 --> 01:49:40,186
We all will one day.

1285
01:49:40,770 --> 01:49:41,645
Soldiers.

1286
01:50:02,936 --> 01:50:03,977
Open the door!

1287
01:50:19,145 --> 01:50:20,270
That's him.

1288
01:50:20,520 --> 01:50:21,478
He's inside.

1289
01:50:22,478 --> 01:50:23,311
Soldiers.

1290
01:50:29,645 --> 01:50:31,353
You won't kill him that way.

1291
01:50:32,353 --> 01:50:33,603
Leave it to us Father.

1292
01:50:34,103 --> 01:50:35,645
He won't get away this time.

1293
01:50:50,811 --> 01:50:52,686
I told you I would spare you.

1294
01:50:52,770 --> 01:50:54,770
Don't make me go back on my word.

1295
01:51:39,436 --> 01:51:40,436
Huh.

1296
01:52:25,020 --> 01:52:28,436
So... You are the priest...

1297
01:52:28,728 --> 01:52:31,353
...who has chased my people
for so many years.

1298
01:52:31,853 --> 01:52:32,853
Yes...

1299
01:52:34,228 --> 01:52:36,853
...but rest assured
I didn't come to fight you.

1300
01:52:36,936 --> 01:52:37,936
Nor I.

1301
01:52:38,186 --> 01:52:39,436
I fight God.

1302
01:52:39,478 --> 01:52:42,311
I'm not interested in
his servants.

1303
01:52:43,478 --> 01:52:44,311
No...

1304
01:52:44,811 --> 01:52:48,020
...you're not fighting God, my son,
you're fighting yourself.

1305
01:52:48,103 --> 01:52:48,977
No...

1306
01:52:49,228 --> 01:52:52,311
No, no, I fought
and I killed in his name.

1307
01:52:52,395 --> 01:52:55,645
We live and we breathe
in his name...

1308
01:52:55,895 --> 01:52:58,936
...why would he want us to
destroy his creation?

1309
01:52:59,228 --> 01:53:00,977
Man kills in his own name...

1310
01:53:01,645 --> 01:53:03,103
...and you're doing it again.

1311
01:53:09,603 --> 01:53:13,436
That is all just very fine words,
God sent you here to kill me.

1312
01:53:14,436 --> 01:53:16,520
God sent me here to save you.

1313
01:53:25,186 --> 01:53:26,395
So...

1314
01:53:26,978 --> 01:53:29,103
So God wants to save me now?

1315
01:53:31,770 --> 01:53:34,645
After he denies me
the right to die for centuries.

1316
01:53:34,977 --> 01:53:37,770
But this is not a punishment,
this is an opportunity.

1317
01:53:38,103 --> 01:53:40,978
Repent, Dracula,
for your salvation.

1318
01:53:43,645 --> 01:53:45,353
She is my salvation.

1319
01:53:49,603 --> 01:53:51,853
But you are her damnation.

1320
01:54:25,645 --> 01:54:27,686
I need a little bit more time.

1321
01:54:54,603 --> 01:54:56,103
Open the door!

1322
01:55:23,270 --> 01:55:24,561
Elizabeta!

1323
01:55:25,436 --> 01:55:26,395
Huh!

1324
01:55:49,103 --> 01:55:50,270
Elizabeta...

1325
01:55:50,603 --> 01:55:52,645
The curse will disappear if I do...

1326
01:55:52,978 --> 01:55:54,645
...you will regain your freedom.

1327
01:55:54,686 --> 01:55:56,145
But you are my freedom...

1328
01:55:56,478 --> 01:55:57,895
...you are my freedom my love.

1329
01:55:58,228 --> 01:55:59,603
Where you go, I go.

1330
01:56:07,936 --> 01:56:09,061
Dracula?

1331
01:56:11,186 --> 01:56:12,645
You believe you love her...

1332
01:56:12,686 --> 01:56:15,936
...but you expect her to
sacrifice her life for you!

1333
01:56:17,311 --> 01:56:18,645
Please don't go.

1334
01:56:18,686 --> 01:56:20,936
Please don't go and stay here.

1335
01:56:20,977 --> 01:56:23,186
Your soul still belongs to God.

1336
01:56:23,561 --> 01:56:27,020
If you truly love her
let her return to life...

1337
01:56:27,103 --> 01:56:29,270
- ...and you return to God.
- My darling.

1338
01:56:30,478 --> 01:56:31,520
Dracula!

1339
01:56:32,770 --> 01:56:34,270
No!

1340
01:56:34,436 --> 01:56:35,520
No!

1341
01:56:37,186 --> 01:56:39,061
Oh!

1342
01:56:39,353 --> 01:56:40,645
Open the door!

1343
01:56:41,061 --> 01:56:43,436
Open the door please my love!

1344
01:56:43,478 --> 01:56:45,186
Four hundred years ago...

1345
01:56:45,686 --> 01:56:48,520
...I asked a priest that
God spare my wife.

1346
01:56:49,186 --> 01:56:50,270
He did not.

1347
01:56:50,561 --> 01:56:51,895
Please!

1348
01:56:52,353 --> 01:56:55,145
Can he hear my pray this time?

1349
01:56:56,186 --> 01:56:58,145
Whether he hears or not...

1350
01:57:01,311 --> 01:57:03,977
Only you can change destiny, my son.

1351
01:57:06,186 --> 01:57:07,311
Save her...

1352
01:57:07,603 --> 01:57:09,311
...and you'll be
in peace for eternity.

1353
01:57:10,978 --> 01:57:12,353
My love..

1354
01:57:20,186 --> 01:57:21,853
So let it be...

1355
01:57:26,061 --> 01:57:27,977
Please, don't leave me my love...

1356
01:57:28,311 --> 01:57:30,561
Hurry up before
I change my mind.

1357
01:57:47,270 --> 01:57:48,520
Please...

1358
01:57:59,895 --> 01:58:00,770
Amen.

1359
01:58:07,895 --> 01:58:09,353
Cease fire!

1360
01:58:42,395 --> 01:58:43,520
Oh!

1361
01:59:23,686 --> 01:59:26,395
Why are you doing
this to me my love?

1362
01:59:38,728 --> 01:59:40,603
Because I love you.

1363
01:59:41,977 --> 01:59:43,395
I love you too.

1364
02:00:59,145 --> 02:01:00,228
Mina?

1365
02:01:43,895 --> 02:01:45,145
The spell is broken.

1366
02:01:45,186 --> 02:01:46,603
Excellent...Excellent...

1367
02:01:46,645 --> 02:01:47,977
Everything is fine now.

1368
02:01:48,145 --> 02:01:50,270
Good. Thank you.

1369
02:01:51,436 --> 02:01:53,145
- Auf Wiedersehen
- Yes, yes...

1370
02:01:54,020 --> 02:01:55,186
Ah!

